Beginner aerial hoop (aka lyra) class

2051

Whiskey and Dust

Please join us for beginner aerial hoop (aka lyra) class.  What is a lyra, you ask? If a trapeze and a hula hoop had a baby, the lyra is it.  It's round, metal and wrapped.  It can spin! If you have always wanted to fly, and never tried...  If you have a desire to take hooping to a higher level... If you like curves, bored with tire swings, and your spinning class goes nowhere, this class is for you.  Do you want to have fun spinning in the air making pretty poses?  I'll teach you how to look and feel fabulous!  Please wear tight clothing that won't fall in your face when you are upside down! Or wear your spandex long-underwear.  I will try to have some skin tight t-shirts.  The more your legs are covered the better you will learn from me.  See you on top, Mandy Pants.

Geology of the Black Rock Desert

2118

Earth Guardians

Ever wondered how those amazing land forms all around Black Rock City? Come and learn from Terry Wright, PhD. retired professor of geology from Sonoma State University. His specialty is bringing the latest interpretations of mountain building and plate tectonics to the creative general public. He will focus on the origin of the bedrock units and mountains of the black rock desert in terms of plate tectonics finishing with the recent history of faulting and lake deposits.

CASTING WORKSHOPS @ DRAGON SMELTER

2206

Dragon Smelter

1.) MOLD MAKING WORKSHOPS The first aspect of using the Dragon Smelter is creating the sand molds to cast art. 2 workshops will occur on playa at the DS (see ARTeries Location map) in the late afternoon @ 5:30 p.m. Tues, 08/30 and Thurs, 09/02. It last 2 hours, involves using steel frames, art “story” boards, sand & binder in a mini-cement mixer and pressure setting sand to create negative mold images & forms to cast into. 2.) Large Casting Events: 5 p.m. to 7 p.m, Wed. 09-01 & Fri. 09-03 @ Dragon Smelter The large casting events involve DS team members plus you, volunteers from BRC “walk-ups”. We will fire the smelter kiln to 1900 degrees, deposit recycled aluminum cans in the crucible, then pour the melted contents into the sand molds to create relief sculptures. 3.) METROPOLIS COINAGE The small coin smelter is a minature DS. small furnace, crucible and cast iron coin dye which is light and totally mobile. We will be operating this during the big casting events at the DS & also daily @ different locations around Burning Man. Check with ARTERies for our daily location if you wish to participate, make yourself a coin on other than big casting event days. This coin is a gifting to reward recycling by all citizens of BRC & also to celebrate the work of Recycle Camp in taking our aluminum cans every year, turning them into funding for Paiute Tribe youth education. For those who participate in this effort, bring their aluminum cans to Recycle Camps we want to convert one or two of them into a “Metropolis Coin” as a gift to reward your effort. 2 to 3 members of our Dragon Smelter team will operate this little machine daily making coins with or for you. 4. P.M. PLAYING WITH FIRE Dragon Smelter spits flames from it’s mouth and tail. You can participate in running these effects at night with us. Come to the DS when you see them start up. Our team will show you how to safety set these shooting flame affects off.

Poly High Tea

2303

PolyParadise

Just what is Poly High Tea? - First, it's a Tea Party. We will be serving Tea and Cookies... All you Polyamorous, poly-curious, and poly-friendly folks out there on the playa are invited to join us for a discussion about the practical issues of loving more than one in an open, responsible multi-person relationship. There are many workable forms of Polyamorous relationship - polyamory is polymorphic! There is much wisdom in the poly community which can be helpful to people trying to make *any* relationship work, monogamous or Polyamorous. There will be a facilitated discussion in which you can get your questions addressed and some of the knowledge in our community can be shared. The Heart of Now

2309

PolyParadise

The essence of the Heart of Now is the practice of being present with your whole self. In The Heart of Now workshop, you’ll come to know yourself more deeply. You’ll discover the possibility of reconnection with your innate beauty, wholeness and be honest with yourself and and with others in a safe circle of love. You can discover those places you’ve felt stuck, while you are supported in letting go. You learn to become aware of those times when you get in your own way, and come to see the choices open to you. You embrace what you desire the most, and deeply commit to letting your dreams and your visions be more important than you past wounds. You will find yourself reconnecting with your innate beauty, wholeness and power in each moment. Heart of Now workshops include numerous assistants to support you and to create a sacred space for transformation. A deeply nurturing environment is created. This teamwork approach deepens the experience of service and camaraderie, where all are able to experience their vulnerabilities, allowing trust and growth. For questions visit our website www.HeartOfNow.org.

Thoughts on Healing

2317

PolyParadise

Almost all of us have something in our lives that we would like to heal. For some it is the challenges of a disease or a physical or mental health condition. For others it is a memory or imprint from our past, a relationship or trauma in our present, or the projection about an anxiety or dread of a future event or situation. This workshop will look at how we can and do use our thinking and subconscious imprints to cause unwanted challenges or create unimaginable healing. A limited number of individual session will be available throughout the week by appointment.

True Mirror Palace Artist's Talk

2345

True Mirror Palace

True Mirror Explained! Every day at 12 noon, the artist Exactly will give a talk on the origins and deeper purpose of the amazing True Mirror - the only mirror that can reflect your true, natural self. Hear how he discovered and perfected it, why its so different, and how to see the magic in it for you. The implications for both personal growth and societal balance from removing one of the key distortions of self knowledge will be explored. Also, the (in)famous Hair Part Theory will be talked about, which explains why some people are so out of balance and why we have such a polarized culture. The real reason why Al Gore lost the election, why Carter is a much better past president, why Andy Rooney, Steve Martin, Hitler, Blagoyovich and many other entertainment and political characters are so unusual, all find explanations with the way they part their hair. and of course, how mirrors have been fooling them even more so because they reflect the opposite hair part!

Yoga to Free Your Voice

2453

Red Lightning

We are all singers. Weaving our reality through the power of our creative expression. We are all gifted with voices that need to be heard. This experience is a blend of Hatha Flow Yoga and Vocal technique, designed to gently release any inhibitions or blocks to complete freedom of expression in a fun and celebratory environment. Appropriate for all levels, accessible to people who have never sung a note yet still helpful for professional singers; the combination of specific Yoga Asanas and flows with vocal training exercises will increase your breath capacity and awareness, develop your range, resonance, and most importantly confidence, and give you the skills to sing safely, and sustainably. This is a joyful experience of healing and empowerment, accessing and expressing your authentic self through movement and sound, training your greatest instrument, and learning to be a YES!

Technomadic Lifestyle Workshop

2805

Camp Nomadia

Why wait until retirement to explore the world? Technology is making it ever easier to work online, so why not take the next step, take your home on the road, and really be location independent? Give in to your wanderlust - come learn how! Camp Nomadia founders Seeder & Serolynne (www.technomadia.com) have been living together technomadically since May 2007, having giving up their conventional fixed homes to create a conscious merging of life, work, sustainable living, travel, community and adventure. They currently base their adventures out of their custom built, solar-powered, and thoroughly geeked-out 17’ fiberglass trailer. Their geographic flexibility has allowed them to travel back and forth across the continent, attending interesting events (and regional burns!), meeting amazing people, and seeing incredible things -- all without sacrificing their ability to run their software development and consulting business, or lessening their ties to friends, family, and community. Some of the other experienced technomads from Camp Nomadia will also be sharing their stories, offering up practical advice and insights to help others make the leap to a life without a fixed home base. This workshop will focus on practical tips on how to leave a fixed-place existence behind and explore a life of technomadism. Topics covered will include selecting the right arsenal of technology to work successfully on the road, constructing your ideal mobile home (wheels, sails, backpacks, or...), and legal issues such as domicile, voting, vehicle registration, and taxes. Immediately after the Technomadic Lifestyle Workshop there will be a Nomadic Happy Hour, so plan to hang around to mix and mingle with a bunch of other current and future nomads. Camp Nomadia is intentionally unplaced this (our third) year, so check for our on-playa location at Playa Info (and likely on our website as well) and come find us.

Where are you?: Map your place

2906

Alternative Energy Zone...

Come find out about this project and describe your own camp! Bring photos if you can! This multi-year project is a cross-disciplinary approach to studying Black Rock City and its inhabitants during the Burning Man Festival. Combining traditional archaeological methods with ethnographic approaches, researchers are collecting and analyzing information about the construction, use, and understanding of the physical environment and the lives and interactions of people within that temporary city. Archaeological methods consist of survey, mapping of individual camps, and surface collection of the city as constructed during the festival. This data will be combined with the results of data collection from the clean-up efforts overseen by the Bureau of Land Management. Ethnographic methods include structured and open-ended interviews, participant observation, virtual ethnography, discourse analysis, and secondary research. Ethnographic findings will be integrated with archaeological data to present a holistic study of Burning Man. In merging archaeological and ethnographic approaches, this project combines analysis of the physical elements of the city with an exploration of the meanings of space and the festival in larger context. Research questions address the creation, use, and significance of physical space and place, the relationship between participants and their environment, temporality and change in ritual practice, and perceptions of self in relation to the landscape. This collaborative project focuses on the materiality and cultural expressions of Burning Man, aiming to uncover the intersecting ethereal and material dimensions of the festival and to study the event's significance for those who create, reside in, and deconstruct Black Rock City.

What are those 5Rhythms Anyway? w/Stacey Butcher

2927

RhythmWave

Want to know more about Gabrielle Roth’s 5Rhythms movement practice? Come to this 90-minute class and be gently guided through each of the rhythms: flowing, staccato, chaos, lyrical and stillness. Each rhythm focuses on a simple movement quality rather than a specific form or set of steps, giving everyone the freedom to move in ways that feel authentic without any pressure to get it right. With a little instruction, the experience of the 5Rhythms® opens us deeply and helps us move beyond self-consciousness to an authentic connection to our body and life force. Using the discipline of each rhythm and the breath as a catalyst for movement, you will be invited to embody, follow, express, and release your own energy. In the end, you will find yourself renewed and reconnected to your own self, feeling fully alive. Taught by Stacey Butcher.

Tune-up Yoga

2968

The Phage

This exercise series is called Tune-up Yoga. It is a hybrid practice combining Yoga, Qi Gong, strength training, and healing to construct an effective, energy producing routine that uses isometric exercises to build muscle capability and core strength, while providing a sturdy platform for those muscles to operate from.  The routine focusses primarily on connecting the shoulders and hips to their associated muscle groups, and is an excellent departure point for peoples own search for health through a variety of healing practices - which are presented within the routine in an introductory manner. The benefits of this exercise style are most noticeable by those who perform tasks such as construction, labor, and computer work, or those who just want a tune-up.

Capoeira

3003

Sukkat Shalom

Capoeira is an afro-brazilian martial art developed in Brazil during the era of slavery. Afro-brazilians camouflaged this martial art with elements of dance and music in order to hide the combative purpose of Capoeira from white slave owners. In this workshop we will teach Capoeira through movement and music.

Looping Seminar

3469

Audioreolae (pronounced...

AUDIOREOLAE...An interactive sculpture/stage/loopstation that allows the participant to create real-time audio loops. Sounds captured may include drumbeats, vocals, guitar melodies or other found sounds. The participant stands under an arch containing speakers, immersed in the sound of their loops, from above and below. The user's figure is framed in a circular opening, a reference to the etymology of the words areola (diminutive form of the Greek word for "open space"), aureole (the traditional "halo" of light around sacred figures in Medieval art) and the literal "audio relay" that is being created. The installation resembles a vertical silver ring, with bamboo fiberglass-clad plywood bases and a semi-transparent fabric covered spaceframe arch, illuminated from within. The looping instructions are very simple, and will be clearly posted. The pedal/trigger will be a large button in the center of the installation, and a 1/4" input, microphone, and electric guitar will be provided. The user interface will be very straightforward and minimal. A participant walking by the sculpture with a djembe could -within minutes- be creating her own drum circle, with literally dozens of versions of herself playing in unison. Amateur singers will be able to experience harmonizing to themselves. Guitar players will be able to lay down the chords to their songs and then write BRC-inspired solo melodies.

Intentional Massage

3586

Sacred Spaces Village

This class will show how massage can be enhanced both for the giver and receiver using the techniques of "touch relaxation", "seeing fingers" and "focused intention". Individuals and couples are welcome (you'll pair up for practice either way). The class will emphasize healing rather than sensual massage, but the techniques are equally applicable to both. 1) Touch relaxation: often the receiver is ignored in massage classes, and I think that's a shame, because all of the really important work has to be done by them, and the giver is but a guide and assistant. This technique is based on focused intention to relax in response to touch. The technique is practiced in pairs during the class. 2) Seeing Fingers: I tend to not even bother with my eyes when giving with massages, because all the important things you can perceive you "see" through your fingertips. This is a skill that can only be learned through practice, and it ties in strongly with the previous concept. 3) Focused Intention: I do some practical demonstrations of what happens when your attention (and therefore intention) wanders during massage, then have a discussion and practice regarding how intention shapes all of what you accomplish during a massage. In the past, people who have attended, especially massage therapists, have been very appreciative of the emphasis on connection between the the giver and receiver vs. specific techniques. Taught by Dreamweaver in the 4th Chakra Temple at Sacred Spaces. I have taught this class with Ascension Tribe several times in the past. I'm self-taught but have been giving and receiving massage for most of my life, and have accumulated my knowledge from a variety of sources, experiential, scientific, and spiritual.

Throat Singing

3676

Camp Gratitude

Throat Singing sounds like a didgeridoo, only anyone can do it without any instrument at all. Learn several Tuvan styles of singing one of which is also used by Buddhist monks as well. Women and men can both throat sing naturally. Through listening and instruction you'll learn one or more of these different styles and how to combine them. I also have been combining throat singing with beat boxing. This is a lot of fun and adds an awesome dimension to beat boxing. Once you learn to do it, and become proficient at it, you can throat sing into a didgeridoo and the resonant tones produce and amazing sometimes hypnotic affect. Come by Camp Gratitude during the day and ask if RememberZ is available. If you catch me in one of many free moments we'll have a lesson. There will also be specific scheduled events as well.

What are those 5Rhythms Anyway? w/Douglas Drummond

3716

RhythmWave

Want to know more about Gabrielle Roth’s 5Rhythms movement practice? Come to this 90-minute class and be gently guided through each of the rhythms: flowing, staccato, chaos, lyrical and stillness. Each rhythm focuses on a simple movement quality rather than a specific form or set of steps, giving everyone the freedom to move in ways that feel authentic without any pressure to get it right. With a little instruction, the experience of the 5Rhythms® opens us deeply and helps us move beyond self-consciousness to an authentic connection to our body and life force. Using the discipline of each rhythm and the breath as a catalyst for movement, you will be invited to embody, follow, express, and release your own energy. In the end, you will find yourself renewed and reconnected to your own self, feeling fully alive. Taught by Douglas Drummond

"Cosmic Singing" with Janis Kelly

3741

Sacred Spaces Village

The Werbeck Technique (www.waldorfmusic.org), based on the work of Swedish artist Valborg Werbeck-Svärdström, is a spiritually enlivened interpretation of the processes involved in singing.  In this interactive workshop, we will work toward developing knowledge of the essential nature of song and summon our "spiritual forces" to assist us as we endeavor to discover our true voices--in all their wonderous purity!  Deceptively simple yet remarkably effective, the Werbeck Technique is the perfect method for every aspiring singer--regardless of age or experience level--and offers lifelong vocal health, longevity, range and FREEDOM! Lead by Werbeck Technique practitioner Janis Kelly (www.janis-kelly.com), a professional musician, music educator, singer-songwriter, recording artist and "Musical Emissary" from Boulder, CO, "Cosmic Singing" is an opportunity to let your voice "come out and play" in a safe, supportive, semi-structured setting!  In Janis' own words, "...even though I studied voice extensively, directed choirs for years and sang professionally for my entire adult life, I never considered teaching voice lessons or coaching singers until I discovered this method.  It--quite literally--allowed me to discover my voice's true potential and has changed my approach to singing at depth." Come on out and let the cosmos sing through you!

Effectively Co-Creating Entheogenic Community

3801

Sacred Spaces Village

There is great change upon the wind, a paradigm shift the likes of which humanity has never witnessed before. We can all sense it. We can feel it in our very bones, calling from the depths of our collective psyche as we draw ever closer toward what Terrance McKenna referenced as the “eschaton”, the ultimate transcendence from a cultural worldview of Logos (Creative Word) to Holos (Holistic & Collective Conscious Evolution). As we move into the New Millenium, facing the apparent and inevitable collapse of old paradigm structures, it becomes ever more vital for us, both individually and as a species, to recognize the fundamental importance of our unified state of existence both spiritually and as conscious co-creators within the Gaian/Human collective. Toward that end, tryptamines, both endogenous and exogenous, provide us all with a unique opportunity and ability to recognize and noetically realize that unified state of universal consciousness that intimately connects us all, to each other, to all of nature and to Source itself. Through the entheogenic experience we can effectively open our hearts and minds to literally limitless possibilities for fostering harmony, beauty, peace, sustainability and greater economic and environmental efficiency, that will allow us as a species to not only survive but thrive upon our planet in the establishment of the age old vision of the Universal Brother/sisterhood of all Humankind. How can the noetic revelations that the tryptamine experience serve us in this process? Come and join Hal Lucius Nation from the Temple of Awakening Divinity in this enlightening and engaging forum where we will collectively envision and discuss these possibilities.

Radical Honesty

4202

PolyParadise

The Radical Honesty technique includes having practitioners state their feelings bluntly, directly and in ways typically considered impolite. People who practice Radical Honesty employ a collection of techniques to shift them out of acceptable norms of "white lying" for the purpose of having a more truthful relationship with themselves and others. In this workshop we will cover Radical Honesty in business, personal interactions, legal situations, relationships, and SEX! Practicing Radical Honesty as an individual is hard, but it doesn't have to be. Me and people like me have developed a calm and peace from this practice. This does involve immense change in those who are used to telling white lies or lies in general. If you are ready for a RADICAL change in your life or you just want to learn about this crazy practice, come to Practicing Radical Honesty for Beginners.

Beaver Yoga

4210

Camp Beaverton

So you want a good start to your day? Then what a better way than Surya Namaskar with the Beavers? Please join CBGB in a 2,500 year old yogi tradition of honoring the sun, Surya Namaskar (Sun Salutation). The Sanskrit word namaskar stems from namas, which means "to bow to" or "to adore." Surya Namaskar, is a series of 12 postures performed in a single, graceful flow. Each movement is coordinated with the breath; Inhale as you extend and stretch, and exhale as you fold and contract. The Sun Salutation builds strength and increases flexibility while removing mental dirt, revitalizing your body, relieving stiffness and restoring balance. This workshop is open to all individuals’ who possess a mat or towel, regardless of your experience. See you on the playa, Namaste!

Compassionate Connecting with James Prieto

4326

Red Lightning

TUE A Taste of Compassionate Connecting: getting to know each other, experiencing our life energy in a group--what's alive in you and me--we get to feel the power of being known and experience a sense of connection and belonging. WED Awareness: acknowledging our observations/judgments, feelings, needs and requests (OFNR). We get to focus our conscious awareness in the directions that we choose. By getting clear on OFNR, we develop competence to begin a journey into greater depths of our being. THU Presence through Self-Empathy: several processes are introduced to help us to become consciously aware of our judgments, observations and the life energy within us. Through these processes, participants will gain valuable tools for self-connection, resulting in feelings of natural compassion, inner-peace and harmony. FRI The Flow of Empathy: after we are self-connected, we now have some free energy to offer our presence and respectful listening to others. We aren't there to fix people, but to help them get clear with their own life energy. In this session, participants will gain practical knowledge of what is empathy and what is not--and will have opportunities to practice and get feedback. SAT Spaceless-Timeless Presence of Empathetic Role Play: empathetic listening can help us to get clear with our pain relating to people who are not physically present. They may have passed on from this life, and we may have some unresolved hurts with them or others. The facilitator demonstrates the power of role plays with participant issues by taking on the spirit of their higher selves--in Christ consciousness.

Following Life/Body Meditation Practice

4586

RhythmWave

Tired of workshops, spiritual practices, seeking and striving and trying to make things happen in the world? How about just Following Life? How about letting go of the striving and seeking and, instead, just connecting intimately with whatever life is bringing to your awareness right now, in this moment? This feeling, this sensation in your body, this thought. How about following this, not analyzing it or trying to figure out, but just allowing it and following it till it reveals life’s wisdom? When we follow life we come into attunement with life. The struggle with life ceases, the tensions in our bodies, emotions and thoughts unwind and we open to the grace that is life. We make ourselves available to opportunities and possibilities greater than anything we could ever plan or strategize with our rational minds. Solutions present themselves, relationships heal and blossom, health and vitality expands and our sheer presence becomes a healing force in the world. Following Life sessions are gatherings where we hold space together to more deeply follow life. Led by experienced facilitators we sit or lie in a circle and practice connecting with and actively following the body sensations, emotions and thoughts that arise in our awareness. We alternate speaking what is arising in our awareness while others listen and follow what is happening in their awareness. We create a collective field that allows everything and anything to be present, to be felt, healed, balanced and transformed. We accelerate our spiritual progress and evolution while becoming more deeply human and connected. I have found these following life sessions to be the simplest, most grounded, yet powerful experience I have ever had and I love how deeply connecting they are with the people I come to meet and know through the practice. – RJ Noble, Bali Tobin Giblin and Charlie Rebich, both long-time meditation practitioners and teachers, will facilitate these sessions on the Playa.

How to Feed the Artists: Loavs&Fishes&PlayaWishes

4603

Feed the Artists

Wherein you will unlock the secrets of the remarkable on-and-off Playa gift of edible bounty that is Feed the Artists. Learn the origins of the simple, radical idea of burning man camps organizing to share their meals with ‘starving artists’ who spend most of their Playa time installing and creating art for the community, and the resulting magic which continues to ensue and multiply with the breaking of bread, be it pita-, gluten-free, or -pudding . Share resources about Reno area food sources, refrigeration, and cooking facilities. Adapt this concept and infrastructure for your next regional burning man event, community or nonprofit event and watch the radical inclusion grow to biblical proportions! Let there be food!

Living Nomadic: Why And How

4650

Camp Nomadia

Why wait until retirement to explore the world? Give in to your wanderlust - come learn how! Experienced Camp Nomadians of all stripes will be sharing their stories, offering up practical advice and insights to help others make the leap to a life without a fixed home base. This workshop will focus on practical tips on how to leave a fixed-place existence behind and explore a life of nomadism. Topics covered will include connectivity, constructing your ideal mobile home (wheels, sails, backpacks, or...), and legal issues such as domicile, voting, vehicle registration, and taxes. Camp Nomadia is intentionally unplaced this (our fourth) year, so check for our on-playa location at Playa Info and come find us - probably around 6 & H.

The Alchemist, Sunny at Rites of Zion

4826

Rites Of Zion

WORKSHOP: THE ALCHEMIST’S PATH: NAVIGATING AND RECLAIMING THE DEPTHS OF YOUR PSYCHE By Sunny Strasburg In this workshop, we will use the dream workbook, The Alchemist’s Path: Navigating and Reclaiming the Depths of Your Psyche (Strasburg, 2007) as an entry point to discuss how each of our lives are the hero’s journey. The workbook, The Alchemist’s Path contains elemental imagery that Sunny painted from a series of “Big Dreams”. These images are based in alchemy and a visual, elemental and spatial narrative. Each of us creates a “life story” in which we give meaning to our lives. The intention of the imagery and exercises in this presentation are to facilitate a beginning of reclamation- to give meaning and importance to our life stories. We will examine how during our lives, we have traveled through four alchemical regions as wee have walked our individual Hero’s or Heroine’s Journey, represented by the elements, water (Solutio), Fire (Calcinatio), Air (Sublimatio) and Earth (Coagulatio). We will view these stories through the lens of Jungian, archetypal, and depth psychology, and explore concepts in mythology, alchemy, archetypal imagery, and depth psychology and how they relate to the symbols in both our waking and dreaming lives. If time allows, we will process experiential exercises which follow the path through the four elements. Using the images from the workbook, we have an evocative starting place. The written and practical exercises are intended to help facilitate the audience’s reclamation and integration of these archetypal realms. “We must let art help us.” (Hollis, 2000)

Alchemy Gender Workshop Sunny @ Rites Of Zion

4827

Rites Of Zion

Intention: The intention and purpose of the Alchemical Gender Circle is to increase understanding of the experiences we have as men and women, both with ourselves and with one another. This is facilitated by enhancing the capacity to listen to another’s experience and creating an intentional space in which we feel open to communicate our feelings. This was developed by me and influenced by the work of Avrom Altman. I have facilitated the circle in many diverse groups of people. Everyone from addicts in resident rehabilitation, parents of autistic children to art collectives and urban family tribes. Process: The process of the circle is in three phases. I am present to act as group facilitator and therapist. During the first phase, the women of the group gather to form a circle. The men in the group hold and contain them by forming a concentric circle around the women. Then the women are given the opportunity to speak about how they feel about · Introduce themselves and what brought them here · Their gender roles, both in their families and society. · What romance and dating/partnerships means to them · What they wish the men in their lives understood about them The men are silent as they listen to the women’s process. During the second phase, the roles are reversed. Without comment, the men and women exchange places and the men move to the center circle and the women hold the space in a circle around them. The men speak about their gender roles and the women in their lives as the women listen to the men’s process. In Phase 3, both the women and men gather in one large circle and speak about what the experience was for them.

What Are Those 5Rhythms Anyway?

4875

RhythmWave

Want to know more about Gabrielle Roth’s 5Rhythms movement practice? Come to this 90-minute class and be gently guided through each of the rhythms: flowing, staccato, chaos, lyrical and stillness. Each rhythm focuses on a simple movement quality rather than a specific form or set of steps, giving everyone the freedom to move in ways that feel authentic without any pressure to get it right. With a little instruction, the experience of the 5Rhythms opens us deeply and helps us move beyond self-consciousness to an authentic connection to our body and life force. Using the discipline of each rhythm and the breath as a catalyst for movement, you will be invited to embody, follow, express, and release your own energy. In the end, you will find yourself renewed and reconnected to your own self, feeling fully alive.

Cuban Salsa Rueda Dance Jam @ RhythmWave

4990

RhythmWave

Salsa Rueda de Casino Rueda simply means "wheel". Casino refers to a place offering and live music and a place to dance. Salsa Dancing. Salsa is a style of music and dance that breaths rhythm and movement into one. Its origin expands from Afro Cuban/ Caribbean/ Latin American beat and culture. What makes Rueda unique is that the dancing is done in the "wheel", as a group, with a “caller” who determines the moves to been done at any giving time. Each move, or "call", has a name. After entering the circle (ideally with a partner, but not 100% necessary,) the leaders advance to the next follower in the wheel after a move or two is performed. This rapid changing of partners makes for a fun and friendly exchange all within the time of one song. Many of the moves also have hand signals as well as names, in order to be able to dance in a loud club setting. The Rueda can be as small as two couples, or as large as a space can hold — as many as a hundred couples. When the circle to too large for the space, concentric circles may be formed. When dancing Rueda, there is a new group dynamic that happens. What is not obvious when watching Rueda, is the new level of awareness required to have a group dance flow smoothly, and look sharp AND keep it fun! Dancers learn to open their sphere of awareness, their peripheral vision, beyond the normal restricted "bubble" of solo or partner dancing. In this way, dancers coordinate and adjust their individual feel and timing and style so as to make the Rueda "click". When this happens, it is very exciting indeed! Guest teacher - Doug Dirt of the French Maid Brigade

Yoga Nidra

4993

Gypsies, Tramps, and Th...

Who needs sleep when there's yoga nidra? Refresh and reorient yourself to the possibilities of the playa. Yoga nidra is a deep meditation practice that mimics the stages of actual sleep; it’s like sleep with a trace of deep awareness that opens portals to your unconscious mind. Swami Satyananda Saraswati is one of the first to have codified teachings from early Vedic literature into eight stages of practice. Christy Anandaconda will lead you through a nidra practice in Swami Satyananda’s framework that includes breath play and exploration, also drawing upon Donna Farhi’s inquiries into current breathing and Blandine Calais-Germain’s discussions on the anatomy of breathing. Bring or create an intention that you would like to work with, something you would like to manifest in your own life. In yoga nidra, this is called a sankalpa, and it focuses your mind at the beginning and end of the practice. Meditate with this sankalpa until the manifestation you desire occurs. Yoga nidra will help you absorb this resolve at the cellular level.

Longevity Stick Art

5026

Cartoon Commune

The sun’s just up, but not too hot yet. Come for an early hour of low impact exercise in the Longevity Stick Art (LSA) discipline of 12 low-impact exercises to build balance, flexibility, strength, mental focus, breathing capacity, and vitality, and open your points and channels. Bring your water and if possible, a stick that’s your height (3/4-1” bamboo, dowel, etc.) We’ll have some available. Master Mai Bac Dao developed the Longevity Stick Art discipline while he was a prisoner of war of the North Vietnamese Army. He helped his fellow prisoners restore and maintain their health through LSA, and vowed that if he was ever freed, he would dedicate his life to spreading its benefits to the world, with the proviso that no future trainer could ever charge for the course. (Sounds like "gifting," eh?) He was freed, settled in Southern California, and started teaching classes of students and future teachers. Today, LSA is practiced widely in Vietnam, and there are dozens of classes weekly around So Cal. Also, LSA is spreading around the US, plus Canada, France, and Australia. Many more details are available at: www.longevitystick.org/Longevitystick.org/Home.html and www.filmbaby.com/films/2341 Master Dao passed away late last year at age 89, and I was privileged to attend his funeral, and his last birthday party, a few months before.

Shibari Basics

5221

Entwined

The word 'shibari' means "to tie" or "to bind", and in Japan it describes the artful use of twine to tie objects. Our Western-style shibari classes will teach you to decorate your own or a lucky partner's body with artistic ropework. Learn versatile single and double column ties, plus playa-friendly wearable designs like harnesses and armbands. Rope will be available for the class - or bring your own, if you have it! We'll even offer you a little something to wear away - to show your friends just how knotty you've been.

Flying Mathematicians vs Inept Trapeze Artists

5490

The Seed

Dr. Kent Northcote on The right brain/left brain divide: a discussion of how the two sides of the cortex cooperate and compete. By examining the functional anatomy and studies of split brain patients, we plan to explore how each cortical side enables us to engage in language, mathematics, empathy and other aspects of our cognitive existence. In addition, we'll explore how each side, despite having different goals, contributes to the single, unified experience we call subjective experience.

EXQUISITE CORPSE DRAWING WORKSHOP

5654

DESERT PEARL CANTINA & ...

Among Surrealist techniques exploiting the mystique of accident was a kind of collective collage of words or images called the cadavre exquis (exquisite corpse). Based on an old parlor game, it was played by several people, each of whom would write a phrase on a sheet of paper, fold the paper to conceal part of it, and pass it on to the next player for his contribution. The technique got its name from results obtained in initial playing, "Le cadavre / exquis / boira / le vin / nouveau" (The exquisite corpse will drink the young wine). Other examples are: "The dormitory of friable little girls puts the odious box right" and "The Senegal oyster will eat the tricolor bread." These poetic fragments were felt to reveal what Nicolas Calas characterized as the "unconscious reality in the personality of the group" resulting from a process of what Ernst called "mental contagion." At the same time, they represented the transposition of Lautréamont's classic verbal collage to a collective level, in effect fulfilling his injunction-- frequently cited in Surrealist texts--that "poetry must be made by all and not by one." It was natural that such oracular truths should be similarly sought through images, and the game was immediately adapted to drawing, producing a series of hybrids the first reproductions of which are to be found in No. 9-10 of La Révolution surrealiste (October, 1927) without identification of their creators. The game was adapted to the possibilities of drawing, and even collage, by assigning a section of a body to each player, though the Surrealist principle of metaphoric displacement led to images that only vaguely resembled the human form.

TANTRIC SHIELDS LEVEL 1

5676

Chakralicious Camp

Hidden within a few yogic lineages lies a secret knowledge of human sexuality. At various times institutions arose teaching and practicing sexual divinity. The teachings were vast, powerful, and hidden. The teachings were kept secret due to the ability of people with weak natures to abuse these teachings for selfish gain and reward. This workshop will be revealing teachings which have been hidden for centuries. This workshop will teach the exercises that courtesans used to train their bodies and energies to remain centered, calm, and untainted by the energy of their lovers. A gentle and very powerful exercise that today is so important for anyone who wishes to remain in their own personal equilibrium. Whether you are in a committed relationship or have multiple partners these exercises allow you to not absorb the bad moods, afflictions, negative emotions and spiritual imbalances. These practices were a sort of sexual shield that allowed tantric courtesans to engage in relations with multiple partners ,while remaining open, yet not be affected by the adverse elements within that person. How important is this in todays world no matter what the manner of relationship you have? These are practices that you can do on your own which will give you full protection from all negative sexual forces. These practices connect and strengthening the actual pathways of sexual energy in the body, doing that we also used to heal sexual traumas and injuries. These are not the sexual ecstasy teachings of Tantric sex. These are the foundation exercises upon which those skills are built. There is a big difference. Come out what that difference is.

Making poi/dart heads

5819

Great Balls of Fire

It's easier than you think! TANTRIC SHIELDS LEVEL II

5870

Chakralicious Camp

TANTRIC SHIELDS LEVEL II Hidden within a few yogic lineages lies a secret knowledge of human sexuality. At various times institutions arose teaching and practicing sexual divinity. The teachings were vast, powerful, and hidden. The teachings were kept secret due to the ability of people with weak natures to abuse these teachings for selfish gain and reward. This workshop will be revealing teachings which have been hidden for centuries. This workshop will teach the exercises that courtesans used to train their bodies and energies to remain centered, calm, and untainted by the energy of their lovers. A gentle and very powerful exercise that today is so important for anyone who wishes to remain in their own personal equilibrium. Whether you are in a committed relationship or have multiple partners these exercises allow you to not absorb the bad moods, afflictions, negative emotions and spiritual imbalances. These practices were a sort of sexual shield that allowed tantric courtesans to engage in relations with multiple partners ,while remaining open, yet not be affected by the adverse elements within that person. How important is this in todays world no matter what the manner of relationship you have? These are practices that you can do on your own which will give you full protection from all negative sexual forces. These practices connect and strengthening the actual pathways of sexual energy in the body, doing that we also used to heal sexual traumas and injuries. These are not the sexual ecstasy teachings of Tantric sex. These are the foundation exercises upon which those skills are built. There is a big difference. Come out what that difference is.

30-min chakra yoga @Camp88 (10:30am Tue-Sat)

5967

88

In honor of "rights of passage," get pass through vibrations from the base of your energy center to the tippy top. Each day of Burning Man at 10:30 a.m., Camp 88 will conduct a chakra-themed, 30-minute yoga session -- from the earthly, grounded energies below, to the spiritual, higher energies above. Each day will include beautiful ambient music, and will correspond to one chakra: - Tuesday: 1st/root chakra; - Wednesday: 2nd/sacral chakra; - Thursday: 3rd/solar plexus chakra; - Friday: 4th/heart chakra; and - Saturday: 5th/throat chakra. The sessions will culminate in a final, 60- to 75-minute yoga and meditation session that incorporates the themes of the top three chakras: 6th (third eye), 7th (crown) and 8th (aura), centering on enlightenment and transcendence. This final session will involve about 30 minutes of yoga, followed by about 30 minutes of silent meditation -- all set to intensely moving, deeply satisfying ambient music.

Sweat Your Prayers at RhythmWave

6135

RhythmWave

"The quickest way to still the mind is to move the body." ~ Gabrielle Roth The 5Rhythms is an in-bodied, out of your mind dance experience not to be missed. It is a simple, powerful moving meditation that anyone – of any age, size, or physical ability - can practice. There are no steps to follow, no choreography to learn, no way to do it wrong. The only requirement is a body that is still breathing, a heart that is still beating, and mind that is still curious! Just like light, sound or ocean waves, a dancing body when moving freely passes through five distinct rhythmic patterns. These patterns continuously repeat themselves in a wave of motion. The 5Rhythms are: FLOWING – the fluid, continuous, grounded glide of our own movements STACCATO – the percussive, pulsing beat that shapes us a thousand different ways CHAOS – the rhythm of letting go, releasing into the catalytic wildness of our dance that can never be planned or repeated LYRICAL – the rhythm of trance, where the weight of self-consciousness dissolves, where we lighten up and disappear into our own uniqueness STILLNESS – the quiet emptiness, where gentle movements rise and fall, start and end, in a field of silence Please join RhythmWave as we return to the Black Rock City for our sixth year with this gorgeous dance/meditation practice that we love to share with you!

Nurturedance @ RhythmWave

6200

RhythmWave

Nurturedance it is a movement form that provides methods for making safe, loving, and nurturing connections between people. By holding, rocking, and cradling each other, a direct path is formed to deep and visceral experiences of nurturance. Some of the movements we do induce mutual trance states by using repetitive circular motion. A hug that evolves into a spiral that is so safe and supported that we enter graceful states of consciousness.

What are those 5Rhythms Anyway? w/Spinnaker

6212

RhythmWave

Want to know more about Gabrielle Roth’s 5Rhythms movement practice? Join RhythmWave's Spinnaker (aka Cynthia Kennedy from Olympia Washington) to this 2 hour class and be gently guided through each of the rhythms: flowing, staccato, chaos, lyrical and stillness. Each rhythm focuses on a simple movement quality rather than a specific form or set of steps, giving everyone the freedom to move in ways that feel authentic without any pressure to get it right. With a little instruction, the experience of the 5Rhythms opens us deeply and helps us move beyond self-consciousness to an authentic connection to our body and life force. Using the discipline of each rhythm and the breath as a catalyst for movement, you will be invited to embody, follow, express, and release your own energy. In the end, you will find yourself renewed and reconnected to your own self, feeling fully alive.

Kundalini Yoga For Beginners

Pink Heart

Spiritual Meaning of "Dust" & "Desert" in Judaism

6854

Sukkat Shalom

Dust and Desert surround us and inspire us in magical and surprising ways at Burning Man. These also happen to be rich, recurring images in Jewish tradition. We were originally created out of dust and we all eventually return to dust, and dust in the wind is a profound reflection of the human condition. Desert is the site of revelation and the unknown, and it is the liminality where we wander between narrowness and wholeness. We'll look at some texts from the Torah, from the ancient Sages, and from modern Jewish thought. And, together, we'll also look inward and outward in new ways.

Pilates

6912

ShangriLa

Core strength is the foundation of Pilates exercise. The core muscles are the deep, internal muscles of the abdomen and back. When the core muscles are strong and doing their job, as they are trained to do in Pilates, they work in tandem with the more superficial muscles of the trunk to support the spine and movement. Centering, Control, Flow, Breath, Precision, and Concentration: These six Pilates principles are essential ingredients in a high quality Pilates workout. Pilates mat exercises will develop strength, flexibility, coordination and balance.

Developing Local and Global Water Ethic

7079

Synesthesia

What is water ethic? What does it mean to be connected to water? the land? each other? What are our responsibilities to keeping water clean and ensuring ample resources for all denominations of society? What are some strategies for engaging people in discussing and finding solutions for water quality and quantity issues? What role does spirituality play in terms of appreciating water and human behaviour towards water and environmental stewardship? We will explore and discuss these questions and more together. There will be examples presented from different places around the world (Singapore, San Antonio, TX, Bangladesh, etc...). We will then break out into groups to brainstorm what a local water ethic would look like in your watershed and prepare a fun pamphlet to educate and attract local citizens to join in the movement.

Longevity Stick Art

7080

Cartoon Commune

The sun’s just up, but not too hot yet. Come for an early hour of low impact exercise in the Longevity Stick Art (LSA) discipline of 12 low-impact exercises to build balance, flexibility, strength, mental focus, breathing capacity, and vitality, and open your points and channels. Bring your water or hydration liquid. We’ll have sticks available for you. Master Mai Bac Dao developed the Longevity Stick Art discipline while he was a prisoner of war of the North Vietnamese Army. He helped his fellow prisoners restore and maintain their health through LSA, and vowed that if he was ever freed, he would dedicate his life to spreading its benefits to the world, with the proviso that no future trainer could ever charge for the course. (Sounds like "gifting," eh?) He was freed, settled in Southern California, and started teaching classes of students and future teachers. Today, there are dozens of classes weekly around So Cal. Also, LSA is spreading around the US and world. Many more details are available at: www.longevitystick.org/Longevitystick.org/Home.html and www.filmbaby.com/films/2341 Master Dao passed away late 2010 at age 89, and one of our campers was privileged to attend his funeral, and his last birthday party, a few months before.

Laughter Yoga

7085

Cartoon Commune

Try on Laughter Yoga to get your Xi flowing like the Playa breeze is blowing! You’ll work up a healthy appetite for whatever your evening activities may be. Start your evenings with the most intense laughter you can experience. We laugh for no reason, other than for exercise, and health. Relieve stress and pain, promote natural healing, and create spontaneous bonds of friendship through laughter. It’s fun! The brainchild of Dr. Madan Kataria in India and practiced by millions worldwide, Laughter Yoga combines Unconditional Laughter with Yogic Breathing (Pranayama). Anyone can Laugh for No Reason, without relying on humor, jokes or comedy. Laughter is simulated as a body exercise in a group; with eye contact and childlike playfulness, it soon turns into real and contagious laughter. The concept of Laughter Yoga is based on a scientific fact that the body cannot differentiate between fake and real laughter. One gets the same physiological and psychological benefits. Find much more info online by searching on Laughter Yoga, but come! Enjoy!

Contact Improv

7090

Cartoon Commune

Come blow your mind experiencing the unique dance known as Contact Improvisation (CI). Cartooning Workshop

7096

Cartoon Commune

Cartoons are a powerful way to make people laugh, or express opinions and feelings.  We know you wanna know how it’s done! And there’s much more to it than just “reproduce this!” We can help you grow and hone your fertile sense of humor. Anyone can do this!  We welcome all levels of skill; you do not need to have any prior training or experience.  Learn all the basic skills like character creation, layout, composition, perspective, and writing. Then take your talent to the next level or even to climactic heights beyond! Brush up on advanced techniques like human and animal figure drawing, proportion, and color.  We end with an improvisational art game using the cartooning skills we've learned. Bring your own sharp pencil or handle one of ours. We’ll also provide the clean sheets (of paper) for you to perfect your best work.

Sacred Geometry & Earth Energies of The Portals

7103

Chakralicious Camp

Sacred Geometry and Earth Energies of the Portals is an in depth presentation of the interactive “Portal” installations by Harlan Emil that employ sacred geometry, color and sound for participants to experience an evolution of consciousness. The golden ratio and the 5 platonic solids that are utilized in their designs will be described, plus the next level of geometries they manifest. It will be explained how the Portal’s designs incorporate the geometric evolution of the Earth’s interactive energy body and relate to the human chakra system. Harlan Emil Gruber is a large-scale sculptural artist who merges his interests in art, design, and science into a unique body of work. He received a degree in Environmental Design from Parsons School of Design in 1985. His diverse career has included art furniture, sound sculpture, future habitation concepts, and large-scale interactive installations. His work has been exhibited in a variety of settings, from galleries in New York City and New Mexico, to the Black Rock desert in Nevada for the Burning Man festival. These installations are now being brought to a variety of events around the world.

5 Rhythms Workshop w/Dagmar Cee

7135

RhythmWave

Want to know more about Gabrielle Roth’s 5Rhythms movement practice? Join guest teacher from Berlin, Germany Dagmar Cee for this 2 hour class and be gently guided through each of the rhythms: flowing, staccato, chaos, lyrical and stillness. Each rhythm focuses on a simple movement quality rather than a specific form or set of steps, giving everyone the freedom to move in ways that feel authentic without any pressure to get it right. With a little instruction, the experience of the 5Rhythms opens us deeply and helps us move beyond self-consciousness to an authentic connection to our body and life force. Using the discipline of each rhythm and the breath as a catalyst for movement, you will be invited to embody, follow, express, and release your own energy. In the end, you will find yourself renewed and reconnected to your own self, feeling fully alive. http://www.5rhythms-berlin.de/

2012 Temple of Alchemy Guided Tours

7155

Sacred Spaces Village

Tour Sacred Spaces' 2012 "Temple of Alchemy" - Learn the science & explore the role of mysticism & metaphor in the language of alchemical principles.Temple curator Rio Gordon writes:"An exploration through the various heretical, metallurgic, Kabbalistic, numerological, and zodiacal principles of the "science" of Alchemy is given in this presentation. Also explored is the role of mysticism and metaphor in the language of alchemical principles, wherein these descriptions are an allegory for spiritual human transformation as described by C.G. Jung and others. The development of images, art forms, and physical scientific practices is noted, as is the impact of this mystical practice on fields as diverse as medicine, chemistry, and meditation. Please join us for this deep look at alchemy as an idea, an act of art making, and a rebellious act of defiance."

Palenque Norte Speaker Series

7160

Above The Limit

Since 2003, Palenque Norte has been the Burning Man reincarnation of the legendary Entheobotany Conferences held near the ancient Mayan temples near Palenque, Mexico. There, Terence McKenna, Jonathan Ott, Ann & Sasha Shulgin, and a host of other luminaries held forth. This year we are featuring many visionary talks, community circles, art and performances on subjects such as: the psychedelic experience and research, technological transformation of the human condition and far future, the weird and the strange, and healing plant medicines. Bruce Damer, Annie Oak, Robert Forte and many others (TBA) will be joining us for three afternoons of lively sessions which will be held in The Crystal Cavern at Camp Above the Limit. Our schedules are posted daily. As is our tradition, all sessions will be later broadcast in the Psychedelic Salon podcast.

Scribe on the future of Burning Man

7247

Shadyvil

Fanning the Flame: A forum on the future of Burning Man culture Is Burning Man still cool? How is the 27-year-old event's skyrocketing mainstream appeal changing burner culture? Can Black Rock City, that temporary desert city, really double in size to 100,000 citizens, as its founder envisions? Or is the future of this culture to be found off the playa, in cities around the world? And who will be calling the shots? Join Steven T. Jones – the Bay Guardian city editor and author of The Tribes of Burning Man: How an Experimental City in the Desert is Shaping the New American Counterculture – for a lively discussion of how this culture evolved and where it's headed. As one of the few journalists regularly working the Burning Man beat, he offers an inside yet independent perspective on this country's preeminent countercultural institution and its role in modern American life.

Tango Class

7363

Tangoed up in Blues

Learn how to partner dance with Tangoed up in Blues (Monday-Thursday). We teach tango and blues classes, follow them up with practice time, then happy hour (often with live music), and dances in the evenings. Tango milongas are Monday and Wednesday, Blues dances on Tuesday and Thursday. In our classes, you'll learn how to do these two social partner dances, how to connect with the music and your partner, how to relax, you'll get to meet and interact with your playa brethren, and you'll dance a bunch. During the guided practice time, you'll have a chance to practice during the day and ask questions of the experienced dancers hanging out. At happy hour, grab a drink, dance and chill. Listen to live music if we have a drop-in musician (or let us know if you you'd like to play some blues or tango music at our camp). And then in the evening, dress up, and come dance the night away. We keep the music running at all hours.

Dance of Liberation with Parashakti

7385

Sacred Spaces Village

The Dance of Liberation is a unique form of movement therapy that heals and frees physical, mental, emotional and spiritual blockages. Utilizing dance, contemporary shamanism, hands on healing, drumming and live DJ, this powerful and beautiful soul work sheds inhibitions and heightens inner awareness in a safe and carefully monitored group setting. Dancers are blindfolded in the shamanic tradition and step beyond their conscious fears and limitations and allow their innermost creative sides to break free. Dancers tune in to sound and movement to take an inner journey exploring a trancelike state of self-discovery and self-realization.

Dancing Freedom: Ecstatic Alchemy

7386

Sacred Spaces Village

Dancing Freedom is a practice of liberation and embodied awakening. It is a somatic, ecstatic and shamanic dance practice supporting the emergence of living oneness. It is fun, engaging and empowering. It heals. It reveals. It welcomes. When we come together we come in peace to create a deep space of shared practice, transformation and community. We gather in ceremony to dance an elemental wave through earth, water, fire, air and ether to reclaim, transform & express the totality of who and what we are. The five Elements are the building blocks of our world as well as alchemical keys to the mystery of divine co-creation. In learning to attune to the elements we can harmonise the inner and outer dimensions of our experience and open to the depths and mystery of the sacred dance of life. As we invoke these primordial forces, they awaken the dreamer within who can assist us to create a deeper relationship to our Selves, others and our environment. Engaging our body, mind and emotions within the relational field is an active and imaginative process that opens the gateways of consciousness for real-time remembrance of our multi dimensional wholeness and unity.

Yoga with Uma

7471

Sin City Stage

Indulge in this challenging, informative, spontaneous, and worshipful experience with Uma, celebrated by New York Magazine as one of NYC's top 5 fitness gurus. Open to all levels. About Uma A life-long belief of "to know it is to live it" found Uma at the doorstep of the famed NYC Jivamukti Yoga Studio of Sharon Gannon and David life. 1997's top grad turned teacher-training director, began to cultivate her roots. Saraswati's "serial chants" and "deft sermons" quickly soared globally as both U.S. and French edition Marie Claire magazines began to pick up on her message. As the foremost Senior Advanced Certified Jivamukti Yoga Teacher, Saraswati mentored hundreds of students. Devotees and apprentices have gone on to open successful yoga studios nationwide. Spiritual master, Shree Maa, initiated Uma into the ceremonial rites of puja worship. Her name Nanda Saraswati, The Goddess of Bliss, was then bestowed. Through intense workshops and rehabilitative knowledge, Uma teaches the authentic experience of becoming your Self. In her pocket she carries a toolkit of ancient teachings: knowledge of Sanskrit language, performance of ceremonial worship, kirtan chanting (5-year tour with famed wallah bhagavan das), meditation, bhakti, and karma yoga studies. Over the years, Uma has had a host of long-standing, high profile, private clients. Uma’s belief that you can't read life, you have to become life; moves you into the depths of your being, so you can peace out. When she is not teaching yoga in downtown NYC, she is ecstatically chanting the name of God in bliss-filled, rock the house, get up and dance kirtans with Lokah. Their debut album, The Ivy Ceiling, is a groundbreaking work that fuses their hearts, souls and voices in a collage of sound. The album features the vocal gracings of Sting and a spoken word introduction by Russell Simmons. Roderick and Anissa Romero of the Seattle underground band, Sky Cries Mary, are featured on backing vocals.

Lecture Traditional and Modern Amazonian Shamanism

7532

Area 51

I became interested in how the shamans utilized sound, chant and music to guide and affect trance states as well as healing. I practiced as a healer at our center (www.bluemorphotours.com), specializing in using ayahuasca and sound to heal depression and generate transcendent experience of consciousness. http://www.nationalgeographic.com/adventure/0603/features/peru.html 4 years ago I started to branch out from ayahuasca and sought to bring the unique qualities of ayahuasca shamanism to music. I wanted to use the music to guide trance states induced by the music. The theory was to guide people to heart, love and direct spiritual or transcendent experience without being told where or how to go. The music itself would guide through the mix of sounds. I started a music partnership with my wife Wendy, who is a 15 year opera, choir and rock singer to create the music. The mix of her traditional musical training with my traditional shamanic training allowed for the right combination to make the music possible.We blended the musical structure found in the shamanism to existing electronic genres like World Music and House. The music itself is electronic with vocals sung by Wendy and me.As for the burn, we have three distinct types of music we could perform. The first would be the chants and icaros of traditional amazonian shamanism (leading ceremonies for groups of people), the second would be to perform our world music and the third, our house music. In addition, lectures on ayahuasca shamanism and the traditional uses of ayahuasca, how it is practiced, apprenticeship, working with elders and the modern uses of ayahuasca for healing. In addition I created a project called Modern Shamanism designed to create a unique form of shamanic/spiritual exploration for Modern people based out of modern life experience. I could lead trances/meditations through this practice. www.modernshamanism.org

Spirituality for Atheists

7550

Above The Limit

In "Religion for Atheists" Alain de Botton argues that "rather than mocking religions, agnostics and atheists should instead steal from them – because they're packed with good ideas on how we might live and arrange our societies." This discussion is about distilling the tools of religions from the dogmas that surround them. (Don't don't throw out the baby with the holy water!) Rather than trying to cover this whole topic in a single workshop, the goal will be to introduce the general concepts while facilitating the sharing of resources (books, articles, quotes, etc.) for people to explore on their own. Please bring something to share.

The Tea House as Community Artform

7609

Fractal Nation

Presented by Annie Oak. The Saraswati Tea House was launched at Burning Man 2011 as a place for guests to rest, rehydrate and participate in the Chinese Gong Fu tea ritual. It's creators continued this project off the playa where it evolved into the Full Circle Tea House and continues to serve at many festivals and gatherings - including the 2012 Burn. This talk will describe how this model of community tea service can be used to provide compassionate hospitality at events where there are often too few friendly spaces that offer water, warm tea, quiet conversation, grounding ritual and a place to nap.

7858

Earth Guardians

Dance as Communication (an interactive lesson)

7965

Tangoed up in Blues

Self expression is cool: flailing, head banging and stochastic gyration is all good fun. But communication is hard if our self expression is not understood. This class aims to cut to the chase and help you build your own vocabulary that reflects you, while imposing as little orthodox structure on your creativity as possible. Where most dance lessons focus on the vocabulary of dance, in this class you will have the opportunity to explore the phonemes of dance. These are the small bits that can be assembled into dance moves, just like we assemble phonemes into words that can be understood by others. Understanding these concepts renders the need to distinguish between one style/vocabulary and another far less important and makes the fusion of many styles and techniques much, much easier. It's like being able to read the phonetic alphabet, or seeing the green lines of binary code behind the Matrix. So here's how it works: We're going to start off with a half an hour or so of these kinetic phonemes (little bits) and we're going to splice in some practice dances to solidify the concepts. Then your teachers are going to to DJ a set using some of the music you've practiced with and employing a playlist designed to illustrate how the social dances can be adapted to a wide variety of cool stuff. So cool in fact, that you will probably want to write down and download when you get home. (or you will experience a rush of feel-good chemicals because you're already familiar with such cool music and that will make you feel cool even though your self-perception is an illusion of your temporal brain chemistry.) During this dance, you may ask your teachers and any other veteran social dancers who may be attending for advice and technique. There won't be any dance etiquette at play here and the next scheduled dance that follows may well be in the nude, so relax, get over yourself and let's have fun.

Panel on Cross Fertilization:

7986

Camp Mystic

A recent study observed participants trapped in an elevator in groups of 10 or 11 people. It turns out that the amount of time it takes a group of strangers to solve an unexpected problem is directly related to its diversity. Completely homogenous groups failed to get out of their elevator at all, while the most diverse groups escaped in a few minutes. This points to what we know intuitively to be true which is the cross fertilization of ideas, methodologies, and perspectives is essential to solving the biggest problems facing humanity today.

There Is Enough Of Everything For Everyone – A Pan

7987

Camp Mystic

There is an unlimited or nearly unlimited supply of everything we could need or want (water, food, love, value, sex, happiness). The single biggest obstacle between us and living in a world where this is apparent to everyone is the meme of scarcity and our belief in its existence. For those of us on the edge of truly surrendering to an abundance mindset, truly walking through the world as fully resourced people, how do we take the last few steps for ourselves and each other? This panel discusses pragmatic methods of transferring from scarcity to abundance in any context for ourselves and those around us.

Nothing new can emerge without first a coming together. Creation -- in all of its infinite forms -- requires an encounter: of people, of materials, of ideas. Everything was born of relations -- of chemistry and community, of labor and love. Every single thing. This simple truth poses important questions: For if everything is born from a cauldron of relations -- from whence comes the spark? And might not some types of relations prove more an obstacle to creativity than its fertile soup? Answers to these questions could in turn help us to answer perhaps the most important question of all: How can we create a more creative world? On Thursday August 30, 2012, TEDxBlackRockCity seeks to investigate the nature of creativity and possibilities of its fluorescence.

Sweat Your Prayers on the Playa w/Dagmar Cee

8167

RhythmWave

5Rhythms is an in-bodied, out of your mind dance experience not to be missed. It is a simple, powerful moving meditation that anyone – of any age, size, or physical ability - can practice. There are no steps to follow, no choreography to learn, no way to do it wrong. The only requirement is a body that is still breathing, a heart that is still beating, and mind that is still curious! Just like light, sound or ocean waves, a dancing body when moving freely passes through five distinct rhythmic patterns. These patterns continuously repeat themselves in a wave of motion.

Bboying 101

8237

Chakralicious Camp

Open class with basic stretching. Briefly explain the fundamental elements of B-boying. Toprock is the foremost opening display of style and introduction to any move. Footwork is movement on the floor with hands supporting the dancer as much as the feet involving variations using knees and threading limbs. Freezes are stylish poses suspending the off the ground using upper body strength. It is often signaled the completion of one's set. Power moves are acrobatic moves that require momentum, speed, endurance, strength, and control creating circular momentum. (advanced) Flavor is about combining all the elements, learning musicality, and developing one's own style. Last 15 minutes of class, all participants will join together in a fun dance cypher to let loose and show what they've learned.

Panel on Cross Fertilization

8243

Camp Mystic

A recent study observed participants trapped in an elevator in groups of 10 or 11 people. It turns out that the amount of time it takes a group of strangers to solve an unexpected problem is directly related to its diversity. Completely homogenous groups failed to get out of their elevator at all, while the most diverse groups escaped in a few minutes. This points to what we know intuitively to be true which is the cross fertilization of ideas, methodologies, and perspectives is essential to solving the biggest problems facing humanity today. The cross fertilization of ideas, methodologies, and perspectives is essential to solving the biggest problems facing humanity today.

Surrender to an abundance mindset - Pragmatic methods of transferring from scarcity to abundance in any context for ourselves and those around us.

TEDxBlackRockCity

8269

Play)A(Skool

Nothing new can emerge without first a coming together. Creation - in all of its infinite forms - requires an encounter: of people, of materials, of ideas. Everything was born of relations - of chemistry and community, of labor and love. Every single thing. This simple truth poses important questions: if everything is born from a cauldron of relations — from whence comes the spark? And might not some types of relations prove more an obstacle to creativity than its fertile soup? Answers to these questions could in turn help us to answer perhaps the most important question of all: How can we create a more creative world? On Thursday August 30, 2012, TEDxBlackRockCity seeks to investigate the nature of creativity and possibilities of its fluorescence. Black Rock City — or Burning Man — the largest intentional community on earth, and one of the world’s most vibrantly creative places, will provide an especially powerful setting for this investigation. On its most basic level, TEDxBlackRockCity will provide a stage for some of Burning Man’s most visionary inhabitants to speak about their ideas and their creations. On a deeper level, it will draw on the very values of Burning Man, whose Ten Principles (radical inclusion, gifting, de-commodification, radical, self-reliance, radical self-expression, communal effort, civic responsibility, leaving no trace, participation, and immediacy) will provide touchstones for the speakers in their talks. Indeed, it is in the spirit of three of these Principles: Inclusion, Communality and Participation, that TEDxBlackRockCity aims to be more than merely a staged performance. For it is intended, above all, to foster creativity among all of its remarkable participants — both on stage and off — drawing on the uniquely dynamic community of Burning Man to concoct an exemplar of that fertile soup churning with creative sparks. TEDxBlackRockCity will take place on August 30, 2012 at 1PM, located at Play)A(Skool —9:45 & Esplanade.

Palenque Norte Speaker Series

8320

Above The Limit

“It’s like TED talks for Psychedelics” The Palenque Norte Speaker Series is a series of lectures focused on altered states of consciousness, psychedelic medicines, and the mystical experience. We will be returning to the Burning Man festival for the first time since 2007, and need your help to make this happen. We’ve put together an amazing schedule of 22 speakers across 4 days which include luminaries such as Alex and Allyson Grey, Paul Stamets, Daniel Pinchbeck, Rick Doblin and many more. The talks will hosted by Camp Above the Limit and be located in the Crystal Cavern, a 40’ dome at 9:15 & B. Check out the full schedule and audio from past lectures at: http://www.matrixmasters.com/pn/ Palenque Norte History The Palenque Norte journey began with the legendary Entheobotany Conferences held at the Chan Kah hotel near the ancient Mayan ruins just outside of Palenque, Mexico. There, Terence McKenna, Jonathan Ott, Ann & Sasha Shulgin, and a host of other psychedelic luminaries passed along many insights, discoveries, and wild tales to the fortunate Tribe members who were there. And it was at the end of the pool where Terence McKenna gave some of his last talks at the Chan Kah. Years later, then in 2003, a few alumni from those conferences decided to have a "Palenque reunion" at the Burning Man Festival, and so we organized a theme camp and lecture series to continue the Palenque tradition.

Transpersonal Phenomena Induced by EDM

8520

Soft Landing (formerly ...

"Experiences of Transpersonal Phenomena Induced by Electronic Dance Music Events" Audrey Katherine, PhD will be presenting her dissertation research which used qualitative and intuitive inquiry research methods to explore the types of transpersonal phenomena that people experience at electronic dance music (EDM) events and how these experiences integrate into day-to-day life. Twelve participants were interviewed and a thematic content analysis was conducted on the data, revealing the following overarching themes: Interpersonal relationships with the numinous, spiritual beings, and human beings are fostered; occurrence of transformative intrapersonal experiences; electronic dance music and its effects on the mind and body serve as a catalyst for experiences of transpersonal phenomena; experiences of a spiritual and mystical nature transpire; emphasis placed on the significance of set and setting. Findings suggest that having experiences of transpersonal phenomena at EDM events enhances health and wellbeing in day-to-day life.

Holotropic Breathwork Workshop with Sheelo Bohm

8596

Soft Landing (formerly ...

Holotropic Breathwork™ is a powerful approach to self-exploration and healing that integrates insights from modern consciousness research, anthropology, various depth psychologies, transpersonal psychology, Eastern spiritual practices, and mystical traditions of the world. The name Holotropic means literally "moving toward wholeness" (from the Greek "holos"=whole and "trepein"=moving in the direction of something). The process itself uses very simple means: it combines accelerated breathing with evocative music in a special set and setting. With the eyes closed and lying on a mat, each person uses their own breath and the music in the room to enter a non-ordinary state of consciousness. This state activates the natural inner healing process of the individual's psyche, bringing him or her a particular set of internal experiences. With the inner healing intelligence guiding the process, the quality and content brought forth is unique to each person and for that particular time and place. While recurring themes are common, no two sessions are ever alike.

Sweat Your Prayers

8656

RhythmWave

5Rhythms is an in-bodied, out of your mind dance experience not to be missed. It is a simple, powerful moving meditation that anyone – of any age, size, or physical ability - can practice. There are no steps to follow, no choreography to learn, no way to do it wrong. The only requirement is a body that is still breathing, a heart that is still beating, and mind that is still curious! Just like light, sound or ocean waves, a dancing body when moving freely passes through five distinct rhythmic patterns. These patterns continuously repeat themselves in a wave of motion. The 5Rhythms are: FLOWING – the fluid, continuous, grounded glide of our own movements STACCATO – the percussive, pulsing beat that shapes us a thousand different ways CHAOS – the rhythm of letting go, releasing into the catalytic wildness of our dance that can never be planned or repeated LYRICAL – the rhythm of trance, where the weight of self-consciousness dissolves, where we lighten up and disappear into our own uniqueness STILLNESS – the quiet emptiness, where gentle movements rise and fall, start and end, in a field of silence Please join RhythmWave as we return to the Black Rock City for our seventh year with this gorgeous dance/meditation practice that we love to share with you!
