BRAF Grant Drop-In Q&A

8782

Everywhere Pavilion

Love the art that you're experiencing on the playa? Wish you had art like this in your home town? Make it happen! Apply for a Black Rock Arts Foundation grant and create interactive art experiences in your community. The Black Rock Arts Foundation was founded in 2001, as a 501c3 non-profit, by several of the founding members of Burning Man. These founders wanted to fund like-minded, community-driven art experiences in the world. BRAF grants awards to about 10 grantees a year, ranging from $1000-$10,000 per project. BRAF's grants program has funded over 90 projects worldwide!Stop by the Everywhere Pavilion and talk to past grantees, members of the Grant Committee, and BRAF representatives who can answer all your questions about getting funding from BRAF. Get tips on proposal and budget writing. Come tell us about your great idea for an art project!

Realizing there are no mistakes

8787

Floristonia

My mind used to constantly be living in the future. As a perfectionist that saw problems everywhere, I would dream about what would make me happy in the future or solve my problems, but it never came by living in the future. Learn how your mind want to escape this moment by dreaming about the future or reliving the past, but true happiness is in the now (current moment). Through connection with my higher self and new actions and seeing that there are no mistakes, I was able to stop escaping to the future and live in the now and find joy. Class will include instructor’s story and lessons learned followed by group sharing and then a 20 minute meditation to experience the now.

Medicine Dance w/Susan Marjanović

8855

RhythmWave

Medicine Dance is a somatic, ecstatic and shamanic dance ceremony that supports the emergence of liberation, interconnectivity and embodied awareness as we move through the fullness of our human experiences. It's fun, empowering and accessible to people - all that is required is curiosity & a willingness to explore one's inner terrain through movement. Using movement, we work with the 5 elements of Earth, Water, Fire, Air and Ether as allies to access the unique Medicine that is encoded within each of us and create a deeper relationship to our Selves, Others, and LIFE. By having an experiential understanding of how these elements work, we gain tools that help us to move through life in a more centered & conscious manner, embracing the shifting currents as exactly the Medicine we need for our healing, growth and expansion into the fullness of our lives. We come together peacefully to create a deep space of exploration, safety, shared practice, transformation and community.

(Nothing but) Flowers

8899

Home Rule

(Nothing but) Flowers You've travelled to the ends of the Earth, cast aside your default life, and willingly peered over the Edge. Now what? (Nothing but) Flowers is a seminar devoted to the propagation of Burning Man core principles in the default world. In keeping with this years theme of the "Cargo Cult" we will discuss situations in which small populations of subjugated people have maintained their beliefs in the face of hegemonic reprogramming efforts. As such, we will discuss the role of the individual in changing the default world to reflect the best of what the Burn represents via various methods of culture jamming and activism. (Nothing but) Flowers a Talking Heads song, and meme for this discussion can be heard immediately following this event @DC not Washington Talking Heads dance party!

BLM Compliance Team Training

8960

Earth Guardians

Last year Earth Guardians volunteered to go out with BLM staff with GPS's and cameras to go out to specific spots in the city, checking for oil drips, grey water spills, black water spills and burn barrel problems. BLM was checking for permit violations and we were along to help Burning Man with the documentation. This year, we'll be going out each morning with Friends of Black Rock volunteers as both LNT advisors and cultural ambassadors with BLM. It's a great opportunity to have 'boots on the ground' and share LNT love. Volunteers will all be getting lunch after each morning shift. (starting at 8:30am-noon).

What are those 5Rhythms Anyway?

9031

RhythmWave

This 2 hour class will gently guide you through each of the rhythms: flowing, staccato, chaos, lyrical and stillness. Each rhythm focuses on a simple movement quality rather than a specific form or set of steps, giving everyone the freedom to move in ways that feel authentic without any pressure to get it right. With a little instruction, the experience of the 5Rhythms opens us deeply and helps us move beyond self-consciousness to an authentic connection to our body and life force. Using the discipline of each rhythm and the breath as a catalyst for movement, you will be invited to embody, follow, express, and release your own energy. In the end, you will find yourself renewed and reconnected to your own self, feeling fully alive.

Plastic-Free Burning Man Workshop

9035

Earth Guardians

What is your plastic footprint? Take a walk through your house (or Burning Man camp) from plastic-packaged food in the kitchen to toothbrushes and shampoo in the bathroom, our world is full of plastic. And at Burning Man, we are sleep in plastic sleeping bags in plastic tents and wear plastic goggles. And how much of our food and water is packaged in plastic? Although some plastics make our lives better, much of it is a problem -- polluting our oceans and beaches and harming our health with toxic chemicals. But what can one person do to be part of the solution? Join us for inspiring stories and practical tips to reduce plastic in your home and on the Playa. Author Beth Terry will share her journey from self-confessed plastic addict to empowered plastic-free activist and explain why we can't just recycle our way out of this mess. You may even get to peek at her (nearly) plastic-free campsite.

Kama Flight Massage with Roland Peralta

9272

Sacred Spaces Village

Kama Flight Massage blends the dynamism of contact improv, the serene flow of Watsu, the deep release of Thai massage and the exhilaration of aerial yoga. It comprises a new somatic modality for reanimating the body with its improvisatory flow and playful exploratory freedom. Supported on a massage table with your body borne aloft on the continually moving fulcrum of the practitioner’s body, the receiver is moved through a wide range of extended postures. Using a suite of practiced movements, such as pivoting his body under different joints of your body, the giver is able to move the receiver seamlessly and weightlessly throughout the course a session. He safely levers the receiver’s body into increasingly extended and pleasurable positions that combine deep hip opening, pivoting and spinal decompression that, collectively, evoke a deep state of surrender.

Personal integration and effects of psychedelics

9316

Sacred Spaces Village

Dr. Kirby Surprise Psy.D.(Sync) will outline the current understanding of the computational model of the mind, and the neuro psychology of how our mind/ brain system processes our experiences. The effects of psychedelics on that processing, and their potential use as personal tools for integration, and what has been discovered from research, will be presented. The lecture will partially answer questions concerning the effects of hallucinogens of brain function, the relationship between brain activity and consciousness, and how focused intent and the use of hallucinogens affect the way the brain processes and integrated experience.

DIY Digital Fabrication

9336

Camp DIY

So you need a thing… A primer on digital fabrication. i.e. Getting stuff made with digital tools. This is a short lecture and longer discussion group on making things with: CNC routers and mills, Laser cutters/engravers. Also touching on water jet, plasma tables, and 3D printers. Facilitated by Shoeshine, an instructor at San Diego’s premier group shop – Makerplace. Topics include: Design software and file formats, 2D vs. 2.5D vs. true 3D, materials, design and strategy for digital production, different processes - pros and cons of each, ways of learning the tools, finding access, online and 3rd party resources, bridging the gap between art and manufacturing, and whatever else the collective mind wants to delve into. Note: This is aimed at folk who would like to make use of these incredible technologies but don’t know where to begin. Though experienced users/makers are welcomed and encouraged to come and add to the discussion. Loads of examples to view, handle, and talk about … Q&A session to follow… and schwag!!!

Blending the Mystery: Gender and Psychedelics

9585

Soft Landing (formerly ...

Mystery and Beauty are biological epi-phenomena that intertwine to produce intellectual and spiritual aesthetics. The mystery and beauty of what I have termed "psychedelic rationalism" will be discussed using the lens of gender. This is a new way of thinking about women's participation and contributions to psychedelic culture, and introduces the idea of a blended rationalist paradigm of psychedelic knowledge. Far from essentialist assumptions that men are from Mars and women are from Venus, this talk will discuss the sociology of male/female cooperation, knowledge, experience, and community-building in psychedelic circles. What emerges is a new paradigm for understanding inner-action/interaction.

In Search of the Philosopher's Stone

9630

Fractal Planet

This is a presentation that narrates a personal healing process through the use of entheogenic agents. These agents provided the transcendent space that allowed inner wounds to be reconfigured into a more manageable and workable form, releasing the soul from inner/outer conflict. Experiences with three different entheogenic agents enabled me to access states of consciousness that fostered healing in my familial relationships by re-framing conflicts, through form of visions and wider understandings, in pictorial, mythological, and transcendent narratives. These experiences in the Other Worlds have been translated into substantial and concrete shifts in the Ordinary World. This journey through the ‘immaterial' considers entheogenic agents as psychological/emotional catalysts for transformation and growth. The Jungian framework of alchemy and individuation has been central in filtering my transformational process and the focus is on its relevance to integrating psychedelic explorations.

Tickling for fits and giggles

Silicon Village

This event is best suited for those with a partner. If you do not have a partner that does not mean you cannot attend. We cannot guarantee you will have a partner to play with, but we will try and match you up with someone or one of our instructors. Do be respectful of others and their boundaries. Just remember we are all here for fun, and we have at least two things in common. We are interested/curious about tickling and we are all burners.

Salsa Rueda Dance

9724

Chakralicious Camp

Come get your latin dance on! In this dance workshop we will learn beginner level Salsa Rueda. Upon completion dancers will be able to recognize about 10 move "calls" and dance them confidently and joyously. Salsa Rueda (aka "Casino de Rueda") is a particular type of circle dancing to Salsa music. It was developed in Havana, Cuba in the late 1950s and early 1960s by the group Guaracheros de Regla. Pairs of dancers form a circle, with dance moves called out by one person, a caller. Many moves involve the swapping of partners creating a fun, synchronized, playful community circle dance.

Laughter Yoga

9737

Cartoon Commune

Start your evenings (5PM: M, Tu, W, F) or days (10AM: Th, Sa) with the most intense laughter you can experience. We laugh for no reason, other than for exercise, and health. Relieve stress and pain, promote natural healing, and create spontaneous bonds of friendship through group laughter. It’s fun! The brainchild of Dr. Madan Kataria in India and practiced by millions worldwide, Laughter Yoga combines Unconditional Laughter with Yogic Breathing (Pranayama). Anyone can Laugh for No Reason, without relying on humor, jokes or comedy. Laughter is simulated as a body exercise in a group; with eye contact and childlike playfulness, it soon turns into real and contagious laughter. The concept of Laughter Yoga is based on a scientific fact that the body cannot differentiate between fake and real laughter. One gets the same physiological and psychological benefits. Find much more info online by searching on Laughter Yoga, but come! Enjoy!

Cartoon Workshop

9742

Cartoon Commune

Cartooning is a powerful art-form that can entertain and influence, but is simple to learn and accessible to all. Come learn from a professional cartoonist to practice this expressive and enjoyable skill. All skill levels welcome; you do not need to have any prior training or experience. Learn all the basic skills like character creation, layout, composition, perspective, and comedy writing. Brush up on advanced techniques like human and animal figure drawing, proportion, and color. We end with an improvisational art game using the cartooning skills we've learned. Supplies provided, or bring your own.

Knife Throwing

9760

8:30 & L

We'll have two classes explaining and demonstrating on how to throw a knife. Part of the explaining will be on why this is NOT a martial art and why, despite everything you've seen in the movies, no one in their right mind would ever throw a knife at a person. It should be thought of as more of a form of object manipulation, like juggling. We'll have one wall for throwing at and a floor board for familiarizing yourself with the weight and balance of the knives. Between classes when we're at our teepee and not wandering around experiencing the wonders of Burning Man we'll be available for more knife throwing fun. Classes will be Tuesday and Thursday 10:00 - 12:00

BRC Philharmonic Orchestra Annual Meeting

9761

Golden Cafe

The Black Rock City Philharmonic Orchestra seeks musicians to bring a performance of Beethoven's 7th Symphony to the playa. Crazy, you say? Impossible? No more unlikely than a deaf composer. -- To create the Black Rock City Philharmonic (a five-year project), we need: 1) section leaders in San Francisco, New York, Western Canada, and Eastern Canada; 2) a bank of Burn-ready instruments; 3) a network of veteran burners who are also skilled musicians; and 4) a road map to guide us to our performance, three or four years down the road. Musicians, enthusiasts, roadies, visionaries, and realists are all welcome to talk about how to bring Beethoven to the playa. Join us for the inaugural meeting of the Black Rock City Philharmonic, to be held at the Golden Cafe in the French Quarter.

TEDxBlackRockCity

9797

Play)A(Skool

TEDxBlackRockCity is a one-day event (August 29, 2013) of talks and performances around this years theme: Paradigm - Shift. Our speakers and performers reflect a wide variety of the creative dimensions of Black Rock City, a temporary city of over 50,000 people formed in the Nevada desert once a year to celebrate art and creative freedom. Black Rock City — or Burning Man — the largest intentional community on earth, and one of the world’s most vibrantly creative places, will provide an especially powerful setting for this investigation. On its most basic level, TEDxBlackRockCity will provide a stage for some of Burning Man’s most visionary inhabitants to speak about their ideas and their creations. On a deeper level, it will draw on the very values of Burning Man, whose Ten Principles (radical inclusion, gifting, de-commodification, radical, self-reliance, radical self-expression, communal effort, civic responsibility, leaving no trace, participation, and immediacy) will provide touchstones for the speakers in their talks. Indeed, it is in the spirit of the 10 Principles, TEDxBlackRockCity aims to be more than merely a staged performance. For it is intended, above all, to foster creativity among all of its remarkable participants — both on stage and off — drawing on the uniquely dynamic community of Burning Man to concoct an exemplar of that fertile soup churning with creative sparks. Please join us for an exciting day at Play)A(Skool and the new Aspire "Learning Center" --- a collaborative interactivity zone created by Play)A(Skool, IDEATE and La Calaca.

Brewing Beer on a Camp Stove

9959

Camp DDI

Brewing beer on the playa? Can't be done. We're going to do it anyways. On a camp stove, with a pot that's too small. By the end of the class, you'll have gone through the process; you'll know how to brew beer! Will you remember by the time you get home? Fat chance. Barring disaster, it'll be fermented, carbonated, and kegged by the end of the week. Drinkable? We'll see. 21+ only

Cargo Cult or Celebration of Colonialism?

9966

Gender Blender

Was John Frum a racist? Is the current theme of BM ignoring the dangers of colonialism, power, and privilege? Explore the ways race, class, gender, power, and privilege affect your experience on and off playa. This workshop is a challenge to the theme that Cargo Cult is all about aliens, visitors returning, and celebrating John Frum. Come join in an interactive workshop that will explore the shadow side of John Frum including the negative impact of colonialism, the glorification of material objects, the destruction of native lands and culture, America's lack of responsibility for military endeavors, and the current impact of this Cargo Cult story. This workshop will explore our shared reality of how racism, classism, and sexism affect our current Burning Man community. We welcome people of all backgrounds to this workshop and to this exploration of how the oppression we were taught in every day society plays out on playa. We will explore the difficulties of the current paradigm and how that affects our ability to form a new experimental community. There will be space to address how we as the BM community want to create change on and off playa.

Open Relationship as a Path of Awakening

9982

Chakralicious Camp

This offering will be a combination of lecture and dialogue on the topic of open (non-monogamous) relationship as a path of awakening. Open relationships, and/or polyamory, are becoming more widely known to the general public as an alternative to the default cultural model of monogamous relationships. One of the first questions that comes up for someone when they first hear about open relationship is "Why?" Why would anyone choose this model of relationship? Certainly at the beginning of someone's exploration of open relationship (and often for sometime to come), it would seem a guaranteed way to bring up ones deepest fears and insecurities. So why do it? We will talk about open relationships and explore answers to these questions, from an unlikely frame, that of spiritual awakening. In my opinion, not only is open relationship compatible with a deep path of spiritual awakening, it may be one of the most profound ways to catalyze and walk that path.

Soothing Sunset Yoga at the Temple

10021

Temple of Whollyness

Start off your week on the Playa with a foundation of deep relaxation, slow breaths and easy yoga poses to keep you feeling resilient and energetic, no matter how much you dance, indulge and play. Special attention will be paid to balancing out all the stimulation the Playa offers your nervous system. This soothing, grounding, mellow yoga practice will be accessible for yogis of all levels. Please bring a mat, as well as a sarong, towel, scarf or belt. We'll meet behind the Temple, as to enjoy the peace it attracts as well as the beauty of the landscape beyond our fair city. Britt Fohrman fell in love with yoga in 1993 and has been teaching since 1997. While her foundation is rooted in the Iyengar lineage, a 10 year struggle with chronic illness inspired her to go deeply into Restorative Yoga, Viniyoga and Buddhism. Having studied therapeutic yoga and movement with many of the leaders in the field, Britt still believes it's her own healing journey, as well as that of her students, that has taught her the most. Along with her steadfast belief in the healing power of yoga, Britt brings resourcefulness and warmth to her classes. Her style of teaching emphasizes individualized alignment, meditative focus and breath guided movement; imbued with levity, compassion and honesty. She encourages you to step out of your head, into your body and on a yoga journey that supports you wherever you are. One of Britt's specialties lies in working with childbearing women, where she also employs her talents as a photographer, doula, childbirth educator and bodyworker. A passionate adventurer and athlete, Britt spends most of her free time traveling, surfing, hiking with her dog and dancing with the performance art group Billion Jelly Bloom. (Who she's camping and performing with on the Playa) Find out more about Britt and her practice at www.brittfohrman.com.

1worldcurrency Money Grows On Trees

10025

1worldcurrency camp

1worldcurrency camp hosts the Granary Receipt Project. A financial revolution and Jubilee. Be gone fiat currency and usury and hello pure money and abundance. Coconut currency anyone? John Frum? Learn the secret lost in the Garden of Eden that money grows on trees. It is the secret hidden from us by the serpent viper money changers. Learn how to destroy all fiat currency and turn it into gods money. Time, technology and resource based currencies. Learn how you can convert your fiat currency into food based currency thus returning the fiat to the bankers who printed it and leaving you with an actual valuable commodity to spend into the economy. Its simple you purchase a bag of grain from a local producer only they agree to store it for you and you get the receipt to trade for other goods or services. Now you have a pure resource based currency. It has more intrinsic value than fiat as it can be eaten. The receipt for the goods must be claimed by a certain date to be valid as the product has a shelf life and the grower storing the grain has to pay for storage. The receipt has the value of the grain paid in dollars and denotes the weight the receipt is good for. The receipt can be traded for the fiat currency value or the weight value. In this way any agricultural community can regain control of their money supply. May peace be with you, Joshua

Rapid Trauma Resolution

10153

"House of Dust" does Ga...

Learn how trauma can be treated effectively in one session of less than 1-1/2 hours. This is an introduction to the amazingly effective, simple and ground-breaking work of Jon Connelly in restoring victims of severe trauma, including sexual violence and war veterans, to full function. (See rapidtrauma.com for more information). The morning workshop will outline the content of an average session, and explain the principles at work that allow for rapid resolution. Attendees will benefit personally by tapping into the human mind’s power to heal and restore proper function after trauma – which is defined as anything stored in the human mind in a dysfunctional way. The afternoon session will ask for volunteers to do a session, free of charge, with an audience observing. Life-changing, all will gain insights that will benefit them in their life and lead to a brighter, lighter, more peaceful and exciting life. Class is taught by David Monroe, who has been a “scout” of healing technologies for years, and is certified in Rapid Trauma Resolution training.

The Black Rock Arts Foundation (BRAF) was founded by several of the partners who founded and produce Burning Man, an annual arts festival in the Nevada desert. The Burning Man event, like no other environment in the world, has created a unique venue for art, and has rekindled one of art’s most valuable functions: connecting community members in creation, curiosity, and wonderment. At Burning Man, we observe how art brings people together, inspires participation and engenders meaningful connections between individuals. The art experienced at Burning Man invites individuals to interact with both the work itself and with their community at large. BRAF was established to bring this modality of creating and coexisting with art to the rest of the world, with the vision that community-driven, inclusive, and interactive art is vital to a thriving culture. The foundation received its 501(c)3 status in November of 2001. Come learn more and see how you can get involved.

The Burning Man Project

The primary purpose of the Burning Man Project is to uphold and manifest the values described in the 10 principles of Burning Man. "Burning Man" is understood not as an event but as a way of life lived consistently with the 10 principles. Burning Man Project provides infrastructural tools and frameworks that allow people to apply the 10 principles in many communities and spheres of endeavors. Sweat Your Prayers w/Eugene Hedlund

10367

RhythmWave

5Rhythms is an in-bodied, out of your mind dance experience not to be missed. It is a simple, powerful moving meditation that anyone – of any age, size, or physical ability - can practice. There are no steps to follow, no choreography to learn, no way to do it wrong. The only requirement is a body that is still breathing, a heart that is still beating, and mind that is still curious! Just like light, sound or ocean waves, a dancing body when moving freely passes through five distinct rhythmic patterns. These patterns continuously repeat themselves in a wave of motion. The 5Rhythms are: FLOWING – the fluid, continuous, grounded glide of our own movements STACCATO – the percussive, pulsing beat that shapes us a thousand different ways CHAOS – the rhythm of letting go, releasing into the catalytic wildness of our dance that can never be planned or repeated LYRICAL – the rhythm of trance, where the weight of self-consciousness dissolves, where we lighten up and disappear into our own uniqueness STILLNESS – the quiet emptiness, where gentle movements rise and fall, start and end, in a field of silence Please join RhythmWave as we return to the Black Rock City for our seventh year with this gorgeous dance/meditation practice that we love to share with you!

Relationship Agreements: Drafting & Honoring

10574

Suspended Animation

Finding ways to remain balanced and effective in your relationships (especially within the context of non-monogamy) can be daunting, as frequent interactions can be rife with assumptions, misnomers, and "but I thought we said's". Yoga Nidra Meditation

10698

Chakralicious Camp

Also known as yogic sleep or sleep with awareness, Yoga Nidra is an ancient tantric practice that is intended to induce full-body relaxation and a deep meditative state of consciousness. Traditionally done in a lying down position Yoga Nidra is a systematic method of complete relaxation, holistically addressing our physiological, neurological, and subconscious needs. Guided imagery and body scan techniques are used to take the practitioner into a deeply relaxed yet aware state. The practice will last 30 minutes. The practitioner begins by quieting the overactive conscious mind, then moves into a meditative state called pratyahara (withdrawal of the senses), gradually finding a state of “ultimate harmony,” in which the brain waves slow down and a subtle euphoria emerges.

TRANSFORMONEY 2.0 - talk by Dadara

10703

Sacred Spaces Village

Even though almost everybody in this world uses money every single day, very few people think about what money is, how it works, and how it maybe might work in a different way. How it could be redefined or even changed. Isn’t money after all just a tool? Our current form of Money, detached from any tangible asset and only backed by our trust, has seemingly taken on the role of an omnipresent Philosopher’s Stone, magically turning any quality of life into a measurable quantity of bigger or smaller heaps of cash, or rather digits on our computer screen. But not all values and qualities can be converted that easily into a pile of banknotes. After all, isn’t what we really value in life ‘priceless’?

Lockpicking Workshop

10788

Black Rock City Hardwar...

Interested in learning how secure locks really are? Enjoy playing with small mechanical puzzles? Want to see if you can, one day, become a true ninja? Then come by and participate in our Introduction to Lockpicking Workshop. I'll start the session off with a presentation on the guts of standard pin tumbler locks (the kind key-locks you'll find on most front doors and many padlocks) and how this translates into lock vulnerabilities and inevitably the potential for picking. The presentation will be repeated as needed throughout the workshop. I'll supply sets of practice locks with escalating difficulty and plenty of tools to go around. The rest of the workshop will go to open play-time and questions. Just bring yourself and an open mind! I'll even bring a few challenge locks for the quick-learners, masochists, and already-experienced pickers. Come and learn how to open today's most commonly used lock - without the key.

Sweat Your Prayers w/Shawn Swanson

10813

RhythmWave

5Rhythms is an in-bodied, out of your mind dance experience not to be missed. It is a simple, powerful moving meditation that anyone – of any age, size, or physical ability - can practice. There are no steps to follow, no choreography to learn, no way to do it wrong. The only requirement is a body that is still breathing, a heart that is still beating, and mind that is still curious! Just like light, sound or ocean waves, a dancing body when moving freely passes through five distinct rhythmic patterns. These patterns continuously repeat themselves in a wave of motion. The 5Rhythms are: FLOWING – the fluid, continuous, grounded glide of our own movements STACCATO – the percussive, pulsing beat that shapes us a thousand different ways CHAOS – the rhythm of letting go, releasing into the catalytic wildness of our dance that can never be planned or repeated LYRICAL – the rhythm of trance, where the weight of self-consciousness dissolves, where we lighten up and disappear into our own uniqueness STILLNESS – the quiet emptiness, where gentle movements rise and fall, start and end, in a field of silence Please join RhythmWave as we return to the Black Rock City for our seventh year with this gorgeous dance/meditation practice that we love to share with you!

Sticks & Stones: Words that Hurt, Words that Heal

11034

Gender Blender

Explore how words both hurt and heal in how we choose to claim our identity. There has been much ado lately in the media and in our lives around words like Tranny, bitch, dyke, slut, cunt, queer, gender queer, tranimal, pussy, fag, ratchet, diva, queen, king, and the list goes on. This workshop will explore what words we use to identify, where those words come from, how words impact us, how words can both hurt us and heal us. This is designed to be a workshop for people of all backgrounds. This workshop will be a safe space for people from all perspectives on these words and all identities to explore these words and the impact they have on us. This will be a time for people to share stories of hurt and sorrow, liberation and joy and to be seen and honored in these stories. The same word that hurts one, might heal another. In this space we request open hearts and minds as we dialogue about this sensitive topic of identity, oppression, reclaiming words, creating words, and living into what these words mean. All genders, races, classes, identities, bodies are welcome and honored always.

Laughter Yoga

11050

Cartoon Commune

Start your evenings with the most intense laughter you can experience. We laugh for no reason, other than for exercise, and health. Relieve stress and pain, promote natural healing, and create spontaneous bonds of friendship through group laughter. It’s fun! The brainchild of Dr. Madan Kataria in India and practiced by millions worldwide, Laughter Yoga combines Unconditional Laughter with Yogic Breathing (Pranayama). Anyone can Laugh for No Reason, without relying on humor, jokes or comedy. Laughter is simulated as a body exercise in a group; with eye contact and childlike playfulness, it soon turns into real and contagious laughter. “Inappropriate” Laughter Yoga is also a possibility, if our clientele are okay with it. The concept of Laughter Yoga is based on a scientific fact that the body cannot differentiate between fake and real laughter. One gets the same physiological and psychological benefits. Find much more info online by searching on Laughter Yoga, but come! Enjoy!

Revolution Camp Discussion

11200

Revolution Camp

Let’s imagine if we had a whole different art and culture. Come on, enough of this “bitches and ho’s” and SWAT teams kicking down doors. Enough of this “get low” bullshit. And how come it’s always the womenthat have to get low? We already have a situation where the masses of women and the masses of people are pushed down and held down lowenough already. It’s time for us to get up and get on up.Imagine if we had a society where there was culture—yes it was lively and full of creativity and energy and yes rhythm and excitement, but at the same time, instead of degrading people,lifted us up. Imagine if it gave us a vision and a reality of what it means to make a whole different society and a whole differentkind of world. Imagine if it laid out the problems for people in making this kind of world and challenged them to take upthese problems. Imagine if art and culture too—movies, songs, television, everything—challenged people to think critically, tolook at things differently, to see things in a different light, but all pointing toward how can we make a better world.Imagine if the people who created art and culture were not just a handful of people but all of the masses of people, withall their creative energy unleashed, and the time were made for them to do that, and for them to join with people whoare more full-time workers and creators in the realm of art and culture to bring forward something new that wouldchallenge people, that would make them think in different ways, that would make them be able to see things criticallyand from a different angle, and would help them to be uplifted and help them to see their unity with each otherand with people throughout the world in putting an end to all the horrors that we’re taught are just the naturalorder of things. Imagine all that.BAsics 2:8

Unlocking the Grid for Poi & Doubles

11233

Super Friends Synaesthe...

Learn the theory that will completely open up the world of flowers and CAPS (continuous antispin patterns) for you and take your spinning to the next level! We will cover basic antispin moves and learn the practice of visualizing the grid you are spinning on. Then we will explore the possibilities that grid has to offer when you apply inspins, antispins, stalls and extensions to each quadrant, in various combinations. Once you know the basic theory and building block moves, you will be able to decipher and break down complex patterns you see other spinners execute. Most importantly, you will be able to experiment yourself and discover endless new patterns to play with. This workshop assumes at least beginning spinning skills. Absolute beginners are welcome, but we will not spend any time teaching the basics.

Palenque Norte Lecture Series

11390

Camp Soft Landing

The Palenque Norte lecture series brings together scholars, visionaries, entrepreneurs and activists to discuss psychedelic topics. The Palenque Norte journey began with the legendary Entheobotany Conferences held at the Chan Kah hotel near the ancient Mayan ruins just outside of Palenque, Mexico. There, Terence McKenna, Jonathan Ott, Ann & Sasha Shulgin, and a host of other psychedelic luminaries passed along many insights, discoveries, and wild tales to the fortunate Tribe members who were there. And it was at the end of the pool where Terence McKenna gave some of his last talks at the Chan Kah. Years later, then in 2003, a few alumni from those conferences decided to have a "Palenque reunion" at the Burning Man Festival, and so they organized a lecture series to continue the Palenque tradition.

Revolution Camp Discussion

11472

Revolution Camp

If you step back and think about it, no wonder they slander communism so much. If you presided over a system that has such glaring, howling contradictions and disparities in terms of how people lived, a system which denied a decent life to the majority of humanity, and weighed them down with tremendous oppression and superstition and ignorance, while a relative handful in a few countries lived a life of unbelievable luxury—but, more than just luxury, they continued to accumulate capital while they fought with each other over who would beat out the other through this exploitation and accumulation of capital—if you stood back and looked at that... Imagine if you said to somebody: go to a drawing board and draw up the way you think the world should be. And imagine if somebody went to the drawing board and painted a picture of the way the world is now, and they said: this is the way the world should be. I mean, there would be tremendous howls coming from all quarters of humanity, saying: What the fuck— that's the way you think the world should be, with these tremendous disparities and people, little children, dying of cholera and malnutrition and other things that could be prevented easily, while a small number battle each other to accumulate more and more wealth from the suffering of this mass of humanity—that's what you think?! ...And it's not hard to see why the ruling class of capitalist-imperialists would employ a lot of people to propagate that idea everywhere they could. If you presided over such a criminally insane system, you would undoubtedly do the same.

On Mon, Jun 3, 2013 at 10:38 PM, Mackenzie Elizabeth Amara ‪‬ wrote:‬ SCENARIO: AS RITUAL, WE DON’T PRE ANNOUNCE THIS. participants enter the space and are immediately blindfolded and given earplugs to put in. we then gently lie them down in a circle, where they silently lay for a few minutes. at some point, someone begins to sprinkle dirt (earth) over them, to represent a burial. at some point, we gently have them rise (still blindfolded) and line them up, placing the hands of each person on the shoulders of the person in front of them. accompanied by drums, rattles, windchimes, flutes, etc. we walk them out to some chosen, semi-remote place on the playa. once there, we paint them with white paint (in ritual markings, not the whole body) and remove their blindfolds and ear plugs. we instruct them to embody various forms of development as we walk back to the original spot - first sliding over the earth, then crawling, then walking, and finally running. perhaps even dancing by the end. reaching our end, we break out into full celebration and incorporation, simultaneously mourning the person that has just died and celebrating the new person that has made the journey back with us.‬‬‬‬‬‬‬‬‬‬‬Mackenzie Amara guides us shouting.

What are those 5Rhythms anyway? @RhythmWave

11686

RhythmWave

Just like light, sound, or ocean waves, a dancing body moving freely passes through five distinct rhythmic patterns. These patterns continuously repeat themselves in a wave of motion. The 5Rhythms are: FLOWING – the fluid, continuous, grounded glide of our own movements; STACCATO – the percussive, pulsing beat that shapes us a thousand different ways; CHAOS – the rhythm of letting go, releasing into the catalytic wildness of our dance that can never be planned or repeated; LYRICAL – the rhythm of trance, where the weight of self-consciousness dissolves, where we lighten up and disappear into our own uniqueness; and STILLNESS – the quiet emptiness, where gentle movements rise and fall, start and end, in a field of silence. Please join Marcia Dancing Heart for an introduction to the 5Rhythms at RhythmWave.

Playa on Tap Talk

11827

Earth Guardians

If you drink bottled water, do you know where your water comes from and do you know what you are paying for? Chances are, it comes from your own municipal water source, but you are paying 700% of your tap water cost. Educate yourself about the sources, costs, health risks and scam of the bottled-water industry. Once you know the facts, you’ll likely never drink bottled water again. You’ll also learn how to break the bottle-habit and easy ways to drink tap water on the playa.

Rootist Yoga Workshop

11898

Sun Guardians

"What is Rootism?" My response to this in short: Rootism is a belief that the truth of our learned existence lies in the Roots of all teachings/truths and beliefs. These truths are different for everyone based on how they we raised and what we resonate with at the time of our learning. As a Rootist, we take the roots of various truths and incorporate them into our own mantra, our own way of living, to become the well rounded person that we wish to be. When you resonate with more than one truth, you are a Rootist. There are many different types of Rootist's. You could be a Christian Rootist, a Buddhist Rootist, or any type of Rootist. The moment you resonate with more than one truth & take the roots of those teachings as your truths, you become a Rootist. Rootism is a lesson that I have learned and come to resonate with over the last few years. I am grateful to share this information with each of you. Please feel free to share this with anyone with whom you feel might be interested. As an offset of Rootism, we have The Rootist's Way. A style of yoga that is in-tentful in it's design and sequences to help to facilitate a certain type of energy clearing and calling in of new energies. Thank you for reading this and for wanting to know more about Rootism. The 8 Principles of Rootism: ∞Principles of Rootism™ 1. Release what no longer serves - nurture yourself & ground yourself 2. Embrace a Creative Vision 3. Move forward on your journey -Take Steps Fearlessly 4. Empathize and Feel what is going on within you & others 5. Motivate yourself & others by Truth – Check the Ecology of the Whole 6. Bridge the Mind & the Heart 7. Evolve a Pro-Sociality Lifestyle & Manifest a Greater Humanity - help others and give back 8. Revolutionize - Reveal Yourself! Open UP! Inner Knowing is Outer Showing The acronym is "Remember"

ACTIVE LISTENING

11911

Whiskey and Dust

Listening seems to be a lost art form. Talking heads on TV scream over each other, meetings are often a cacophony of entrenched opinions or even chatting with a friend can sometimes seem like a spewing of 2 people without each listening to the other. But when listening is used to your benefit, it presents the amazing opportunity to enrich your life with the stories of those around us, offering perspective, wisdom and connection. In this workshop you will learn the skill of active listening. You will learn how to engage those around you with a silence that demonstrates your deep compassion, understanding and interest for the story they are sharing with you.

"Naming-it" to others

11933

Camp Contact

The workshop is about building communication tools. Specifically "Naming it" is about speaking your emotional truth to another person. I, the facilitator, used to find it very difficult to have those difficult conversations we have to have with romantic partners, friends work colleagues and so forth. However during my training to become a psychotherapist, not only did I learn how to "name-it", but I learned how empowering it was to do so, and my relationships and life has improved as a consequence. As a result I want to gift the playa some of the skills I have learnt by offering a series of "Naming-it"workshops, so I can make becoming a better communicating easy and fun. So please join me and come "name-it".

Nurturedance

11937

Camp Contact

Nurturedance is a movement form that provides methods for making safe, loving, and nurturing connections between people. By holding, rocking, and cradling each other, a direct path is formed to deep and visceral experiences of nurturance. Some of the movements we do induce mutual trance states by using repetitive circular motion. A hug that evolves into a spiral that is so safe and supported that we enter graceful states of consciousness. If you are looking for ways to enhance your relationship with your partner, this may be useful. Relating in non-verbal, non-linear fashion can have an effect of breaking through barriers of relating on new and different levels. People report that using these methods deepens and re-invigorates their relationship.

TEDxBlackRockCity 2014 "Smart & Simple" With this year’s theme, we will present inspirational change agents and guarantee an afternoon of ideas worth sharing. We believe that there is no more fertile venue in the world to explore Smart & Simple than Black Rock City — also known as Burning Man. The fundamental qualities of this city in the desert – the world’s largest intentional community – are freedom, experimentation, and participation, precisely the conditions in which new approaches to old (and emerging) problems can be conceived and realized.For most people who come each year to Burning Man, the shared dream is to take the values and aspirations of the Playa back to their homes, workplaces, and communities; to practice and promote the Ten Principles, not just on the playa once a year but all the time everywhere. Transforming the ‘real’ world is a formidable challenge and a powerful dream. Join us at TEDxBlackRockCity as we share the dream and encourage responsibility for making change happen.

It teaches us how to release stress, stay focused, clear the chatter from our minds and auric fields, and eliminate free radicals from our bodies. When we connect with Gaia, we begin to realize that we are all safe and well provided for. We learn to understand our greater truths and to let go of fear, anger, guilt and anxiety. This allows us to establish a connection with our divine authentic self. Whether you are a seasoned meditator or novice, you are invited to experience an ancient Eastern meditation breathing technique that has been passed on from master to master for centuries to achieve self-enlightenment. We will utilize ancient grounding techniques and a guided meditation to establish our connection with Gaia, help transform our outlook, and feel more grounded in our everyday lives.

Circus Play Time!

12112

Circus Boot Camp

YOU ALWAYS WANTED TO RUN OFF AND JOIN THE CIRCUS... NOW YOU CAN! Come earn your clown nose at Circus Boot Camp. You've seen feats of skill on the Playa, and who hasn't dreamed of running off to join the Circus. Heck, half of y'all probably still dream in acrobats and clowns. At Circus Boot Camp, we'll teach you to juggle, unicycle, hoop, slack line, trapeze, crack a whip and indulge your childish fancy in other circus-inspired arts. Already a circus pro? Come test your mettle on our slackline; dance your clown shoes through the obstacles of irony; pass clubs with seasoned semi-professionals; try your hand at the Valley of One-Wheeled Doom!!

Sonya Sophia - Tapping into WOMAN ~ EFT

12125

Red Lightning

Sonya Sophia is a gifted empath, master level healer and “Love Activist” with 25 years of experience in the healing arts. She is the founder of The Sophia School of Living Arts, an online healing school that produces The World Tapping Circle. This is a 90-minute, life enhancing, interactive Tapping experience within a global, online community Sonya teaches physical and emotional healing using EFT, Emotional Freedom Technique or Tapping, as a foundational practice giving people a visceral experience for their real-time transformation. Those who’ve studied with her now bring the healing gift of EFT to their own families and communities. She brings feminine wisdom, deep love, loads of laughter plus life-changing releases to audiences and workshop participants worldwide. Her mission is to support the healing of humanity and facilitate Heaven on Earth. Her standing-room only workshops have been offered in the UK, France, Italy, the Netherlands, Germany and all over the United States, from California to New York City. As a guest speaker at the International Alchemy Conference, Leaders Causing Leaders Conference and the Conscious Life Expo, she’s brought the miracle of Tapping to ever expanding audiences. Sonya continues to teach at Transformational Festivals, including her two favorites – The Rainbow Gathering for over 20 years and Burning Man for the last 7 years. Sonya Sophia invented and published the format for EFT Circles, now widely practiced throughout the world. She has created recordings to help people come to life, activate Divine Purpose and step into their true power.

Heavenly Yoga - Divine

12324

ShangriLa

Heavenly Yoga - Joy

12327

ShangriLa

Take it easy this afternoon! Joy is a very gentle Hatha Yoga class that holds poses longer and works with relaxing the entire body, while bringing awareness to all the muscles, joints, veins, tissues and organs. It also uses the breath to go deeper into opening restricted areas in the body and exploring the benefits of meditation. A truly joyful experience.

Heavenly Yoga - Paradise

12328

ShangriLa

Paradise is a series of 26 poses. Most Yoga poses (asanas) are performed twice and held for a minute or 30 seconds. Heat is created in the body and used to allow the muscles to go deeper and safer into the poses. It eliminates the risk of injuries, promotes sweating and helps to release toxins. This class uses the same routine every time. Hot Yoga is a way to experience paradise on earth.

Mat Pilates @ ShangriLa

12359

ShangriLa

Come & play early! Core strength is the foundation of Pilates exercise. The core muscles are the deep, internal muscles of the abdomen and back. When the core muscles are strong and doing their job, as they are trained to do in Pilates, they work in tandem with the more superficial muscles of the trunk to support the spine and movement. Centering, Control, Flow, Breath, Precision, and Concentration: These six Pilates principles are essential ingredients in a high quality Pilates workout. Pilates mat exercises will develop strength, flexibility, coordination and balance.

Creative Visualization: Picture your future

12506

Dr Feelgood Advice Boot...

Join us for a guided creative visualization meditation. We will help you picture the perfect day 10 yrs in your future. The process works by subconsciously shifting your decision making over the next 10 years eventually making your vision a reality. You don't know what that day looks like? Don't worry, most people don't, but your subconscious already knows what is important to it. The more amazing and compelling the vision that you let emerge, the more you will be drawn to it. How? Most people make between 80 to 400 decisions a day. A rich, compelling visualization with a lot of sensory "hooks" can shift those decisions towards your perfect future because the right choices will feel "right". We will start with a mindfulness of breath meditation, a gratitude exercise and then wake up the morning of your perfect day and explore it through a guided process. After, we will ask a few of those interested to share their visualization with the group. We look forward to sharing your future day together. Dr.Feelgood

Sessions can be given in 15 minutes to 1 hour depending on the participants needs. Reiki is joint practice between healer and participant. The more open and accepting of the universal healing energy you are, the more powerful your session will be for both yourself and the healer. So come, relax, be yourself and enjoy the gift of Reiki at Camp 88. Love&Light always all ways.

Heart Circle

12713

Sun Guardians

The North American First Nations regarded the circle as the main symbol for understanding life's mysteries. They have observed that all of life was circular movement which could be seen everywhere throughout nature. Man looked out on the physical world through their eyes, which is circular. The Earth is round, and so is the Sun, Moon and planets. The rising and setting of the Sun follows a circular motion. The seasons form a circular movement. Birds build their nests in circles. Animals marked their territories in circles. In the old days, tribes lived in circular homes called tepees and their communities were arranged with the tepees in a circle. Indeed, to the Natives, the whole of life appeared to be circular.

[freespace] around the Globe

13005

Everywhere Pavilion

What happens when you get a building for $1 and give it to the community to run?... [freespace] The experiment started in June of 2013 and has quickly spread to cities around the world. A [freespace] is a gathering place for people to come together, to create, teach, learn, and share the things which they are truly passionate about, and strengthen connections between individuals and communities through art, events, and long term projects. Anything goes as long as it is both free and inclusive like an urban version of the “permission engine” on the playa. Currently there are 8 open [freespaces] in 6 cities on 4 continents. There are communities developing in 26 locations and 18 different countries around the world. [freespace] co-founders and organizers from around the world will host an information session, discussing the [freespace] model and facilitating Q&A. Help bring the playa ethos back to your community.

Sacred Geometry Art Class

13086

Mycodelic Forest

Free-form art class with sacred geometry in the mix! For over 2,400 years, the Golden Mean has fascinated mathematicians, biologists, artists, musicians, architects, psychologists and mystics alike. This “transcendental number,” 1.618… and the sacred geometry derived from it are the blueprint for all organic matter and growth on this planet. Artists such as Phidias and Da Vinci incorporated this sacred geometry into their works, believing it to create an aesthetically pleasing balance. Come to the Mycodelic Forest and learn a little more about sacred geometry and different ways to add it into your art while painting some works of your own. We’ve got acrylic paint, brushes and several sheets of heavy artist’s paper for you. (You might want to bring a hard, flat surface to work on, if you have one).

Relationship Survival at Burning Man

13147

Chakralicious Camp

Part of the magic of Burning Man is the altogether unexpected nature of what will happen. For one week, we step outside of our usual selves, finding God in a phone booth, discovering your true authentic self in the eyes of clown on whip-its, or stumbling upon the Barbie Death Camp and Wine Bistro. But, all this novelty can be a strain on your relationship. Once you combine it with the heat, dehydration, strange substances, strange food and even stranger campmates, your previously lovely and wonderful partner may seem to have turned into some sort of dusty alien. A dusty alien you can barely stand. Fortunately, you can avoid a visit to the Costco Soulmate Trading Outlet with a bit of preparation and foresight. In this workshop, led by open relationship coach and multiple-Burn veteran Marcia Baczynski, you’ll find out everything you need for your relationship to not only survive, but thrive, at Burning Man. We’ll cover: Your #1 secret weapon for avoiding fights on the playa (especially those really, really stupid ones) - The real reason the Burn makes or breaks relationships - What to do when you have different ideas of what “fun at Burning Man” means - A quick and easy way to get the most out of your time together -- and apart - Simple and practical steps you can take now to make your Burn together the best one ever Plus, you’ll walk out with your own personalized guide for staying connected, getting what you both need and having a blast during your time in the dust. Whether you’re a virgin burner or going home yet again, join us for a hilarious and practical workshop that will help you make sure you get to enjoy your camp, your costumes and your favorite co-conspirators. Because “going to the Burn” shouldn’t mean “sitting in a hot tent processing.”

The Psychedelic Eucharist

13197

Cosmicopia

Psychedelics have been an integral part of the counterculture since they burst onto the scene during the revolutionary 1960s. Half a century later, human civilization still finds itself poised on the edge of social and ecological annihilation. The psychedelic experience, like much of the exotic infusions that shaped the consciousness of the 60s, has been all too easily appropriated by consumer capitalism, transformed into just another gimmick to satisfy our addiction to instant gratification. This talk will explore an alternative, alchemical interpretation of such experiences that serves to undermine the sort of ecologically and politically alienated mode of consciousness that continues to perpetuate capitalist social relations. Psychedelics are an invitation to re-imagine what it means to be human beings.

Recovering the Soul of the Cosmos

13205

Cosmicopia

For the past several hundred years, Western society as a whole has been primarily influenced by the dogma that matter is as that is actually "real," and that the best way to understand reality is to approach it like a machine, seeing how its parts function. This approach, while making possible the unprecedented technological advances that began during the industrial revolution, have likewise led us to an unprecedented state of emergency - primarily seen in the ecological crisis. To remedy the alienation and disenchantment that this still dominant paradigm has propagated, we must recover those dimensions of the cosmos and of our own being that can't be found or explained in material terms. Opening our "archetypal eyes," as depth psychologist James Hillman put it, can help us to once again move in rhythm with the threads of meaning that weave through our lives and the cosmos as a whole.

Learn to Dance Kizomba!

13222

Camp Awesomeness

Learn the basics to this fast-becoming popular dance from Angola & Cape Verde called Kizomba. Not to be confused with the Columbian-born latin workout program "Zumba", Kizomba is more like Tango mixed with other Latin dances like Salsa and Bachata. With proper top frames and booty-shaking bottoms and legs, this couple dance is becoming the most popular "latin" dance in Europe and USA, almost at par with Salsa and Bachata. Whether you're a couple or alone, there's always room for everyone to learn the basics and show of some new moves in the playa or in the default world. Facilitated by: E aka #DanceNinja at Camp Awesomeness

Chakralicious Camp

Sex, Spirituality, and Pain

13231

Chakralicious Camp

We are at a critical time in human evolution where these aspects of ourselves can no longer be separated. They are the cornerstones of our existence, the elemental factors that have come to determine our life’s quality. We have a deep burning desires for passion and creativity, eroticism and the unknown! We want to give and receive love more powerfully, more receptively!! We want to fully heal any wounds or past traumas around receiving love. We want to feel healthy, alive, and vibrant! And yet, we so often leave our bodies in search for something more. As pain continues to rise at an exponential rate in our working class society we are uncertain how to use one of our most powerful energy forces in our body, our sex, our dan tien, our bodies inner wisdom and guidance to heal us. We remain disconnected from these forces! We desire to capture those moments of extacy, those moments where the divine enraptures us and our central light explodes and penetrates through us, releasing the forces of the mind and the controlling locks held in the muscles of our bodies. This workshop will incorporate Feldenkrais techniques focused on opening up our 2nd and 4th chakras and reconnecting to our bodies, as well as group and partner interaction and discussions.

Introvert Awareness for Introverts and Extroverts

13270

PolyParadise

Have you noticed how much we hear about introverts and extroverts in the media and in everyday conversation these days? Do you know which one you are? Are you clear on what these terms really mean? Susan Cain has written a fantastic book called Quiet:The Power of Introverts in a World That Can’t Stop Talking. Her Ted Talk has been viewed over 9,000,000 times! Susan maintains that our society is set up to favor and promote extroverts. Yet it’s estimated that over a third of us are introverts. Introverts sometimes feel devalued and not aware of the unique gifts they have to share with all of us. Through a combination of lecture, group discussion, and experiential activity, you will learn how introversion and extroversion are defined. You will learn how being an introvert can impact on your family and work life. You will learn how to become more sensitive to the needs of both introverts and extroverts. You will learn how to find out more about introverts and extroverts.

But take your inspiration to write your Ploem while in Black Rock City! *** Please note that this event takes place at the tower in the Cafe, not the tower on the open playa. *** MWF 11-noon, TT 5pm-6m, in the large Ploetry installation in Center Camp Cafe.

Rootist Yoga Practice

13576

Sun Guardians

"What is Rootism?" My response to this in short: Rootism is a belief that the truth of our learned existence lies in the Roots of all teachings/truths and beliefs. These truths are different for everyone based on how they we raised and what we resonate with at the time of our learning. As a Rootist, we take the roots of various truths and incorporate them into our own mantra, our own way of living, to become the well rounded person that we wish to be. When you resonate with more than one truth, you are a Rootist. There are many different types of Rootist's. You could be a Christian Rootist, a Buddhist Rootist, or any type of Rootist. The moment you resonate with more than one truth & take the roots of those teachings as your truths, you become a Rootist. Rootism is a lesson that I have learned and come to resonate with over the last few years. I am grateful to share this information with each of you. Please feel free to share this with anyone with whom you feel might be interested. As an offset of Rootism, we have The Rootist's Way. A style of yoga that is in-tentful in it's design and sequences to help to facilitate a certain type of energy clearing and calling in of new energies. Thank you for reading this and for wanting to know more about Rootism. The 8 Principles of Rootism: ∞Principles of Rootism™ 1. Release what no longer serves - nurture yourself & ground yourself 2. Embrace a Creative Vision 3. Move forward on your journey -Take Steps Fearlessly 4. Empathize and Feel what is going on within you & others 5. Motivate yourself & others by Truth – Check the Ecology of the Whole 6. Bridge the Mind & the Heart 7. Evolve a Pro-Sociality Lifestyle & Manifest a Greater Humanity - help others and give back 8. Revolutionize - Reveal Yourself! Open UP! Inner Knowing is Outer Showing The acronym is "Remember"

Vinyasa Flow by Lisa

13645

Sun Guardians

We will be going through a series of poses that will move you through the power of inhaling and exhaling. Vinyasa movements are smoothly flowing and almost dance-like, with synchronized breath and movements. Vinyasa has both mental and physical benefits. Physically, sweat expels toxins and re-energizes your body and can be an easy to challenging physical workout, mostly depending on you and where you take your practice. Mentally, the synchronized breathing relaxes your mind and helps to release any blockage of energy flow throughout your body.

What are those 5Rhythms anyway? w/Marcia

13647

RhythmWave

Just like light, sound, or ocean waves, a dancing body moving freely passes through five distinct rhythmic patterns. These patterns continuously repeat themselves in a wave of motion. The 5Rhythms are: FLOWING – the fluid, continuous, grounded glide of our own movements; STACCATO – the percussive, pulsing beat that shapes us a thousand different ways; CHAOS – the rhythm of letting go, releasing into the catalytic wildness of our dance that can never be planned or repeated; LYRICAL – the rhythm of trance, where the weight of self-consciousness dissolves, where we lighten up and disappear into our own uniqueness; and STILLNESS – the quiet emptiness, where gentle movements rise and fall, start and end, in a field of silence. Please join Marcia Dancing Heart for an introduction to the 5Rhythms at RhythmWave.

Cory Doctorow on The Internet of Things

13722

Camp Soft Landing

"The Internet of Things: Poisoned at Birth by the Inkjet Printer Business-Model." The computers that engulf your body (cars, planes, houses) and that you insert into it (prosthesis, pacemakers, hearing aids) are subject to a ridiculous Clinton-era copyright law that lets their manufacturers lock them so that you can't use app stores or replacement parts of your choosing -- but worse than that, to keep you locked in, the law criminalizes telling you about flaws in the devices that you depend on for life and limb. It is only in this way that a new world reveals itself — as strange, yes, but perhaps also closer to world in which we dream. In 2015, TEDx BlackRockCity will be an opportunity to open and reflect ourselves in new ways, to a new world, in which we are all transformed by ideas that matter.

Devi Flow Yoga w/ Juju Namjai

13904

Red Lightning

Devi Flow is a strong vinyasa practice with elements of dynamic heart opening movements (mudra-asana-prana-bhakti dance) set to undulating world rhythms and the sounds of the ocean. Devi Flow is a power class that strengthens the core, uplifts the spirit, calms and focuses the restless mind. Devi Flow is an evolution of intentional movement and yoga blended soulfully to ignite the warrior spirit. Using simple mudras, heart opening dynamic movement and a traditional vinyasa flow, Devi Flow awakens the inner warrior/goddess within all Yogi’s - while receiving therapeutic benefits from the practice. Together we will explore as a collective and express as individuals, creating harmony with breath, beauty with movement; all to the sacred heartbeat within unique original music and the sounds of nature.

Clashing With Cash

14100

Chakralicious Camp

Money Shadows: Creating Abundance by Dancing with The Unconscious. The Playa is a magical place where the gifting economy reigns. Yet, some of us spend big bucks preparing and getting to Black Rock City. So, even here money talks even if we pretend not to listen. Still some of us struggle off the Playa with not having enough, wrestle with “it is never enough” or believe financial issues are too taboo to explore out loud, Perhaps for the first time, we will really listen to the voices we hear in our heads or the ones we don’t even know exist which block us from creating abundance and banishing scarcity. Up Your Game with Sexy Skills!

14323

Chakralicious Camp

Imagine, you’ve just met someone you’re highly attracted to. You’re having a wonderful conversation and you feel the excitement building in your chest. You’re at the point where you know you want to take it to the next level. It’s the moment of no return. This moment of tension is both one of the hottest moments of attraction and potentially one of the most awkward. How do you know if the other person is at the same desire level? How do you assess their openness to touch, to a kiss, or more? A kiss or initial touch is relatively low stakes, but what happens when things heat up? What happens when you’ve just overstepped a line and can feel their withdrawal? These nuanced moments of initial sexual attraction can be the hottest of our lives. But we’re never really taught how to navigate highly sexually charged moments with someone completely new. What does it mean to fully take responsibility for these moments so that when we’re done everyone involved feels totally awesome? In this workshop you will get a much deeper understanding of the nuances of initiating and negotiating hot and sexy connections. -Boost your sexual self-confidence -Know how to feel your “fuck yes!” and your “Oh no!” and everything in between. -Understand when and how to bring up "the conversation" so you don’t deflate all the sexual turn-on! -Gain clear sexy communication skills to keep it hot while still conveying important information. -And learn the number 1 reason why these skills will make you the sexiest person on earth!

Moving Meditation Contemplative Dance

14341

Camp Contact

Dancing with the Mind of Meditation This Contemplative Dance workshop offers you an introduction to a variety of movement meditation techniques. We'll sense and feel the way that energy moves through the body with Qi Gong practice. We'll explore somatic training and the Body/Mind practices of Developmental Movement and Experiential Anatomy. We'll investigate our relationship to form, space, and each other through Viewpoints Space Awareness and Mudra Space Awareness. This class is a laboratory where we'll be working with the energy that animates our bodies. We'll be exploring how energy moves when the body moves and how mind can direct energy. We'll learn to harness the power of the breath and focus of the mind to attain higher performance outcomes. The work is toward attaining a greater depth of expression of personal energy, achieving grace and ease in a variety of movement patterns, developing an equanimity of all body parts as initiators and supporters of movement in space, and gaining the ability to dance ecstatically with great amounts of energy without loss of awareness of where you are and what is around you. Everyone is welcome from dancers seeking to bring contemplation into their dance - to those wishing to bridge their sitting practice to their walking meditation practice to the rest of their active lives - to people who have never danced or meditated before.

Laughter Yoga

14343

Camp Contact

Laugha Yoga is an ancient yet new idea of combining the practices of yoga, prolonged intentional laughter and Radical Forgiveness. This combination is extremely potent and effective. This dynamic practice energizes, enlivens and brings us greater confidence. Laughing Yoga has many health benefits among which are a boost in our immunity and lowering stress levels. Forgiveness is an ability we can develop to renew our relationship with our self and others. Laughter is a by-product of the joy and heightened sense of interconnectedness.

Relating from Our True Nature

14372

Camp Contact

Relating from Our True Nature This workshop is designed to be simultaneously deep and playful. We begin with a deep dive into our truth—our true nature—which is simply a letting go and a knowing of who we always already are, beyond our ideas about ourselves and others: a simple direct undeniable knowing of our clear deep heart-mind-being. We will ground ourselves in this present moment and connect with our higher self and cultivate our intentions, desires, and wishes for the night. Using movement, stillness, and humor we bring awareness and acceptance to ourselves and our conditioning. Through simple spontaneous body movements you embody and express your truth(s) and your true being. Finally we move into connecting and relating with each other while staying connected with our self. This process will be facilitated with some simple relating exercises and is a chance to see through our ego and conditioned habitual ways of relating and being. We invite a sense of humor to simply seeing ourselves and the conscious and unconscious games we play. Bringing awareness to our patterns opens the possibility of playing with them and responding from our clear deep heart mind space, rather than reacting. Respond from awareness rather than react from habits. We live from our true nature rather than our conditioning. We dance.

NurtureDance

14418

Camp Contact

Nurturedance is a movement form that provides methods for making safe, loving, and nurturing connections between people. By holding, rocking, and cradling each other, a direct path is formed to deep and visceral experiences of nurturance. Some of the movements we do induce mutual trance states by using repetitive circular motion. A hug that evolves into a spiral that is so safe and supported that we enter graceful states of consciousness. If you are looking for ways to enhance your relationship with your partner, this may be useful. Relating in non-verbal, non-linear fashion can have an effect of breaking through barriers of relating on new and different levels. People report that using these methods deepens and re-invigorates their relationship.

Navigating Altered States & Ayahuasca

14475

Chakralicious Camp

Imagine, you’ve just met someone you’re highly attracted to. You’re having a wonderful conversation and you feel the excitement building in your chest. You’re at the point where you know you want to take it to the next level. It’s the moment of no return. This moment of tension is both one of the hottest moments of attraction and potentially one of the most awkward. How do you know if the other person is at the same desire level? How do you assess their openness to touch, to a kiss, or more? A kiss or initial touch is relatively low stakes, but what happens when things heat up? What happens when you’ve just overstepped a line and can feel their withdrawal? These nuanced moments of initial sexual attraction can be the hottest of our lives. But we’re never really taught how to navigate highly sexually charged moments with someone completely new. What does it mean to fully take responsibility for these moments so that when we’re done everyone involved feels totally awesome? In this workshop you will get a much deeper understanding of the nuances of initiating and negotiating hot and sexy connections. -Boost your sexual self-confidence -Know how to feel your “fuck yes!” and your “Oh no!” and everything in between. -Understand when and how to bring up "the conversation" so you don’t deflate all the sexual turn-on! -Gain clear sexy communication skills to keep it hot while still conveying important information. -And learn the number 1 reason why these skills will make you the sexiest person on earth!

The discussion will then be followed by a 2 hour Yoga & Qi Gong class which will blend together the elements of ancient India (Yoga) and China (Qi Gong) to provide a dynamic moving meditation focused on providing a balance of both Yang (active) and Yin (passive) elements, that will conclude with a healing Yoga Nidra (conscious deep sleep) meditation - leaving you empowered, focused, and energized - ready for the burn and the new year. "

Open Relationships as a Path of Love and Truth

14612

Chakralicious Camp

This workshop will explore how open relationships can be way to transform the opposition between Freedom and Love into the mutual support of Love and Truth. Many people in relationships struggle to reconcile their Love for each other and desire for deep partnership with their desire for the Freedom to connect intimately with others. The default model for relationship in our society, monogamy, makes explicit the underlying belief that Freedom and Love exist in opposition with each other. But what if our desire for Freedom in relationship is covering a deeper desire, namely that we want to know, and be assured, that we can speak and honor our deepest Truths, and Desires, even, and especially, while in we are in Loving committed partnerships. So what if, instead of talking about Freedom, we talked how to create a relationship where it's safe to speak our Truths, including all of our desires (even for others), and know that we will still be Loved? Join us for a conversation about how open relationships can be created from a place deep Love and commitment to Truth.

Mead Workshop @ the BuzzInn

14695

Silicon Village

Buzzinn to the dHive bar and delight in humankind’s original ambrosia! Mead is the oldest alcoholic beverage known to man & we aim to share with you how easy it is to make at home. A honey based wine, mead requires a very small investment on your part. The variations of style are endless as you can make mead with fruit, ciders, herbs, different kinds of honey, dry or sweet, (i.e. has remaining sugar), bubbly, (like sparkling wine), or still. We will explain how to make it, where to get it, and even have demo equipment available. 21+ and over can sample different varieties we've made and brought to share. You will come away with an understanding of: Early Discoveries of Mead, Mead in Religion and Culture, & the Techniques of Making Mead: -Overall concepts that mixing water, honey and yeast starts a reaction to convert the sugars in the honey to alcohol and release carbon dioxide gas. -The equipment needed such as a 1, 3 or 5 gallon water bottles, airlocks, tubes to siphon off the mead from the ‘lees,’ (sediment at the bottom of the fermentation container), bottles, and a few other items such as cleanser to keep everything clean. -Selections of honey to make mead and how the type of honey influences the end result flavor and the same for yeast selection. -Selections of ‘adjuncts’ which influence the flavor of your mead: the addition of spices such as cloves or cinnamon (known as metheglin), or the addition of fruits such as raspberries or strawberry (melomel). We will finish up with tasting different styles! Bzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzz!

Bucky Dome open-house

14738

Things That Swing

Did you just spend a few hours setting up a dome? Then you should check out this new method of dome building that sets up in under an hour. Using the geometry of the truncated icosahedron, aka Bucky Ball, this dome frame features uniform pole lengths, isometric vertices, and a modified tensegrity system to stabilize and distribute loads. 15’-25’ diameter domes can be erected by two people in under an hour.

Laughter Yoga

14772

Cartoon Commune-Green R...

Start your evenings with the most intense laughter you can experience. We laugh for no reason, other than for exercise, and health. Relieve stress and pain, promote natural healing, and create spontaneous bonds of friendship through group laughter. It’s fun! The brainchild of Dr. Madan Kataria in India and practiced by millions worldwide, Laughter Yoga combines Unconditional Laughter with Yogic Breathing (Pranayama). Anyone can Laugh for No Reason, without relying on humor, jokes or comedy. Laughter is simulated as a body exercise in a group; with eye contact and childlike playfulness, it soon turns into real and contagious laughter. The concept of Laughter Yoga is based on a scientific fact that the body cannot differentiate between fake and real laughter. One gets the same physiological and psychological benefits. Find much more info online by searching on Laughter Yoga, but come! Enjoy!
