Longevity Stick

14905

Cartoon Commune-Green R...

The sun’s just up, but not too hot; clothing is optional here, so adults only, please. Come for an early hour of low impact exercise in the Longevity Stick Art (LSA) discipline of 12 low-impact exercises to build balance, flexibility, strength, mental focus, breathing capacity, and vitality, and open your points and channels. Bring your water or hydration liquid. We’ll provide sticks for you. Master Mai Bac Dao developed Longevity Stick Art discipline while he was a prisoner of war of the North Vietnamese. He helped his fellow prisoners restore and maintain health through LSA, and vowed if he was ever freed, he’d dedicate his life to spread its benefits, with the proviso that no trainer could ever charge for it. (Like "gifting," eh?) He was freed, moved to Southern California, and taught classes of students and future teachers. Today, weekly classes abound in So Cal, around the US, and the world. See: www.longevitystick.org/Longevitystick.org/Home.html and www.filmbaby.com/films/2341 .

Cartoon Commune Green Reflections’ Eco Camp Tour

15173

Cartoon Commune-Green R...

Build up your eco-consciousness for Playa life. We’ll show you how we reuse, recycle, repurpose, and redesign. See our solar cooker, rocket stove cooker, solar power, evapotron, and much more. Consider the Playa’s ecosystem, and the gear and food that are right for a trip into this world.Be ready for your next vacation with Mother Nature. Nothing seems more natural than spending time in nature, but it’s easy to forget eco-attitudes when away from concrete cities. We’ll discuss prepping for a trip, being alert to pack only what we need: e.g., first aid kit, weather-appropriate clothing/gear, water & food. We leave packaging at home to minimize trash on-Playa. If we can, we pre-buy local fruit, veggies, and nuts; pre-make dishes and seal them in lightweight reusable containers. Reuse these to avoid disposables. We seal our food well, store trash, compost and recycle our waste. We’ll be happy to hear your own ideas and consider them for additions to our Playa eco-practices.

ShangriLa

Knife Throwing Class

15374

Gigsville

We'll have two classes explaining and demonstrating on how to throw a knife. Part of the explanation will be on why this is NOT a martial art and why, despite what you've seen in the movies, no one in their right mind would ever throw a knife at a person. It should be thought of as more of a form of object manipulation, like juggling. We'll have one knife throwing wall and a number of floor boards for familiarizing yourself with the weight and balance of the knives. We'll have knives for practice but feel free to bring your own. Classes are Tuesday and Thursday 10:00 - 12:00

Circling

15435

Yummy RUMInations

Circling (also know as InterSubjective Meditation) is an organic, in-the-moment interpersonal process that’s equal parts art form, meditation, and group conversation — all designed to allow a visceral experience of connection and understanding of another person’s world, celebrating who and where they are right now. It’s practicing using our genuine curiosity to better understand and become a connoisseur of another person’s world though present moment awareness while breaking through the assumptions and projections we have about each other.

Cocoon Workshop

15659

Camp Contact

The Cocoon is performed architecture. Inside the Cocoon we physically create the space and structure with our bodies. Chanting, dancing and other ritualistic strategies will generate a massive collective energy. No experience necessary! For the generally creative and outgoing. It manifests a collective spirit as we create a sacred space for transformation and rebirth. Inspiration, identity and rebirth take morphing, sculptural form. The Cocoon is a hand-crafted stretchy fabric enclosure created by Sherry Aliberti, an architect and performance artist based in New York City. Structurally, these postures represent a scale model of an architecture and materiality based on the forces of the body. The Cocoon Project is a multi-disciplinary collaborative performing the Cocoon with movers, live projected visuals and soundscape. The performed-installation conveys a primordial one-ness of many bodies within the sheer membrane. CocoonNYC performs site-specifically in galleries, music venues and alternative spaces. The Cocoon experience can be emotionally powerful for every age and/or background.

Introduction to Thai Yoga Massage

15877

Floristonia

A 90-minute workshop introducing Thai massage theory and techniques to anyone who would like to enjoy being able to offer their benefits to friends and family. No bodywork experience is required. Thai Massage is an ancient bodywork practice which combines acupressure, energy meridian stimulation and yoga-like stretching. This is an Ayurvedic version of Shiatsu which encourages great relaxation and rejuvenation. The recipient, fully clothed on a floor mat, continues to remain passive, while gently and fluidly, yoga-influenced stretches are applied to them. There are many positive effects including stress-reduction, increased flexibility resulting in injury prevention, muscle spasm relief and the treatment of a wide variety of orthopedic complaints. This work is also a conscious, meditational application of Metta (love and compassion) that leaves both the giver and receiver with a life-affirming feeling of peace and connection. Jennifer Gillmor is a Senior Practitioner at Thai Massage Toronto, a Holistic Table Massage Practitioner and a Yoga Teacher at Yogaspace in Toronto, Canada

Raving Stick Workshop At The Castle

15913

Celtic Chaos

Have you ever been at a festival and looked on in awe as some guy raves to his heart’s content while carrying a glittery lampshade on a stick? But random objects hanging from sticks covered in lights and glittery things… that’s totally our thing! That, my friend, is what we call a “raving stick” and no self-respecting raver should venture out onto the playa at night without one. Raving stick materials will be provided on the day by Celtic Chaos, but attendees are more than welcome to bring along their own personal additions. Lecture: OUR FUTURE IS FEMALE

15937

Planetarium Camp

The threat of nuclear war, the next extinction level event, climate change and economic enslavement, all point to the unsustainability of our current trajectory. With all of humanity's advances, why can't we achieve peace and prosperity for all? The underlying cause of our failure might be gender inequity: women are our most underutilized natural resource. Past societies which overcame war and poverty were governed similarly to us, with one difference-- the existence of a fourth branch, consisting of post-menopausal women only. Following this historical precedent, how can we restore women's voice in government? And, can we do it in time?

Circling

16494

Camp Contact

Circling is an organic, in-the-moment interpersonal process that's equal parts art form, meditation, and group conversation - all designed to allow a visceral experience of connection and understanding of another person's world, celebrating who and where they are right now. It's practicing using our genuine curiosity to better understand and become a connoisseur of another person's world through present moment awareness while breaking through the assumptions and projections we have about each other. Different than sitting on a meditation cushion by yourself, Circling is a relational practice. And though it works exquisitely in intimate relationships of all kinds, it can be applied in ALL areas of life because it's so organic, non-analytical, effective, and fun.

Tantric AUM

16560

Naked Heart

The AUM (Awareness Understanding Meditation) Workshop is based on the understanding that in order to find its silence, the western mind first needs to express its tension and stress.The aim of the AUM Meditation is to consciously transform stress and negative emotions into positive creative energy, and to create personal well being and peace through a social process of Awareness, Understanding and Meditation.It is divided in twelve stages that allows you to experience all shades of your emotional life ‚Äì anger, love, sadness, laughter ‚Äì and to express these emotions in a protected and safe environment.Once emotional awareness and intelligence are mastered, it becomes easier to express emotions in a healthy way, resulting in more effective communication skills and a greater sense of personal empowerment. The fear of expressing all our feelings diminishes, freeing us to make a genuine choices about how we act. Unspoken positive and negative feelings can create blocks in our relationships with friends, colleagues and loved ones.Through experiencing the AUM, relating becomes clearer, more honest and more fun. the AUM also allows you to reclaim to joy of simply being alive.Bring a pillow or cushion

OUR FUTURE IS FEMALE

16678

Zerodrome

The threat of nuclear war, the next extinction level event, catastrophic climate change, corporate compromise of our food supply, and economic enslavement, all point to the unsustainability of our current trajectory. With all of humanity's advances, why can't we achieve peace and prosperity for all? The underlying cause of our failure might be gender inequity: women are our most underutilized natural resource. Past societies which overcame war and poverty were governed similarly to ours, with one difference-- the existence of a fourth branch, consisting of post-menopausal women only. Following this historical precedent, how can we restore women's voice in government? And, can we do it in time?

How to Save the World in 2 Simple Steps

17722

Camp Mystic

So you have a meditation practice...now what? The challenges that humankind is facing can seem unsolvable. Problems like climate change, terrorism and the food crisis. Emily Fletcher suggests that the solution to these complex problems may be much simpler than we think. Meditating twice a day can not only help to optimize your personal performance, it can help to up-level the state of consciousness of innovators and world leaders (read everyone) who are positioned to solve the more complex challenges the world is facing. You may laugh, you may cry but you will definitely leave lit up about leaving the world better than you found it.

Camp To CampUS

17771

Camp Mystic

There are more than 50 million innocent displaced people that had to flee for war, poverty, injustice or climate change. The average stay of a refugee in a camp is 17 years. Since WWII the hosting and management of a refugee community in such camps has not changed. Till the day of today refugee camps are harsh survival environments where people risk exploitation, are hopeless and rules of the strongest apply. After being involved in the epicenter of the refugee crisis on the Greek island of Lesvos I came to the knowledge that there is such a big difference to be made in this global issue if we would stop seeing refugees, victims of injustice. Instead we should approach them as individuals with talents, opportunities equal to our own standards and with the same needs. We should be aware that if we would invest in people that have lost everything this investment will be returned to us in gratefulness and willingness to contribute in their own succes. You get what you give... In creating communities that thrive you should start with environments that inspire. On Lesbos, the epicenter of the refugee crisis in Europe last year, I witnessed the similarities in dynamics between hosting refugees on a refugee camp and hosting a crowd on a music festival. We believe many insights from the festival industry can be integrated to redefine a refugee camp from a Spartan fashionlike environment to an inspiring festivallike experience. Adding to the festival game innovative solutions/companies, educational programs and integration of the refugee community in the management and self-sustainability of their camp will create an environment of harmony and dignity that will be an example in how to change a global issue into an opportunity that can serve humanity on a global scale. Join me in this quest to redefine the global concept of a refugee camp to a campUS.

We'll show you how and you'll leave with a crystal of your own, supplies permitting. Mon-Fri 2-3pm Dark Wednesday.

Pinhole Camera Photography with Pinhole Project

17929

Illumination Village

Come check out our pinhole camera and play with us, we do pinhole photography! Pinhole Project has brought to the playa twelve very large pinhole cameras created out of 50-gallon cardboard barrels. Join us in our annual pilgrimage to use old school pinhole photography on the playa. The Pinhole Project exposes 30 x 40 inch sheets of light sensitive gelatin silver paper. We work with 12 pinhole cameras, created out of 50-gallon cardboard barrels. This size is uniquely suited for capturing the incredible scale and immense diversity of art and culture at Black Rock City. Under the red safelights of the darkroom, photosensitive paper is inserted into the camera body. Exposures range from 40 to 300 seconds, where concentrated beams of sunlight are funnelled through the pinhole and into the camera, creating a negative image of the recorded subject. We maintain a desert darkroom in a shipping container, where we gather to processes, develop and fix about one hundred photographs each Burning Man. These unique images are then exhibited in Illumination Village, Center Camp Cafe, and off-playa. The pinhole camp has been creating large-scale portraits with festival participants since 1999.

Elephant Expressions

17988

Elephant Expressions/Ra...

A ten part, ten year art project based on the Ten Principles of Burning Man. This year, in name of "Radical Self Expression" we sent out five hundred vinyl toy elephants to kids all over the world and asked them to express themselves by decorating them. We are then taking those elephants and displaying them at Burning Man under The Man as part of the Guild Workshops piazza. Our aim is to bring awareness of the importance of creativity in a child's life. Lack of funding has stopped art programs in many public schools across the country. We are figuratively and literally putting the crayon back in the child's hand. We are also bringing 10,000 elephants to the playa this year and letting burners express themselves by decorating the elephants, and gifting them to fellow burners. We chose to create a vinyl elephant for the kids to decorate because of the elephant's outstanding memory. We are building positive experiences in children that we want them to remember for a lifetime. We also sculpted the elephant into the shape of the Vitruvian Man, as a wink to this year's Burning Man theme.

Tribal Tantra Heart Opening Puja

17991

Naked Heart

You are invited to this Heart Opening Tantra Puja. A Puja is a devotional offering. Through this sacred ceremony we can realize of the true nature of the Self and experience into the state of total oneness. This Tantra Puja is a way of honoring and adoring the divine that dwells within each of us. What is a Heart Opening Puja? Watch here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=osqSdVTIZ_4 This is a "station" puja. There is an inner and outer circle. One rotates and with each rotation you have a new partner. Each partnering is an opportunity to fall in love with ourselves through the eyes of another. The stations are subtle, elegantly simple and this is their potency. The tantric arts invite us into our own heart in an ease full way. One of the most exquisite is this ceremony where we open to an embodied experience of witnessing the divine in all and thus the diving in ourselves. Open to the possibility of adoration, forgiveness, unconditional love and experiencing your true and higher self in the span of a few short hours.

Bucky Dome Open House

18095

Things That Swing

Check out this new method of dome construction that sets up in under an hour. Requires no tools, special skills, or strength to assemble. Using the geometry of the truncated icosahedron, aka Bucky Ball, this dome frame features uniform pole lengths, isometric vertices, and a modified tensegrity system to stabilize and distribute loads. 15’-25’ diameter domes can be erected by only two people.

All You Need Is Love

18183

Guild Workshops -- At t...

Hi everyone, come and get PLASTERED! ;o) We humbly invite you all to “Becoming the Master/Mistress of Stones: The Arts of Buon Fresco!” Welcome to the Burning Man Guild Workshops! For the first time ever, Burning Man is hosting a series of workshops in a Florentine piazza-style format to have Masters of various craftsmanship skills teach our students the arts of the Renaissance. We, The Three Faced (Stone) Wench Workshop/Guild, are offering a series of classes you would love to attend! Here’s the scoop: Apprentices will learn the various actual old time techniques over several days to create a fresco (block) from scratch to take home. As part of our commitment to up-cycle, we will utilize and recycle actual (old foam insulation) building materials. Participants will learn to recreate various historical stone mixtures that compromise the the surfaces of the block, complete with plastering, cartooning, and finally the stages of painting the actual fresco with pigments. This artifact creation will be followed by (and applied) techniques to 'age' their artwork with the patina and craquelure of passing time. The result? A beautiful, yet portable and tangible, aged piece of buon fresco that becomes their momento of inspired learning at Burning Man. ;) Upon completing your fresco block, you will receive a Playa Plastered Master of Arts certificate, authorizing you to be plastered anywhere on the playa! That’s not all! We are offering a unique community project/event, and we invite everyone to participate with your hearts (and energy): We are accomplishing a recreation of Gustav Klimt’s Beethoven Frieze (Ode To Joy), with a slight twist on the theme: “All You Need Is Love.” The secco fresco artwork will stretch across several large panels, a moving tribute of the people lost at Orlando, Florida, and of our experiences at Burning Man. Please join us! ;o) Youth ages 12 and up welcome.

Bridges to Another Life

18196

Camp Mystic

"Exponentially accelerating technology, population and development imply that the vast majority of all technological progress has occurred within living memory, yet the basic template for industrial civilization hasn't changed much since Hiroshima. Merely tacking organic food and iPhone apps onto the suburban consumerism of the fifties sells both humanity and technology short. Rather than leaping into the unknown however, or embracing an interested vision, most people rightly stock with what they know, even as it ceases to inspire, or even to make sense. Experimental communities can showcase the possibilities technology and abundance have made available, preparing the disaffected to make a shift from consumerism to more advanced forms of society. "

Come Make Pinhole Photographs with Pinhole Project

18421

Illumination Village

Remember that lesson in art class where you made a camera out of an oatmeal box? Pinhole Project invites you to check out our cameras, do an art tour, and make art on the playa! Each year, we shoot, develop and fix about one hundred photographs on the playa each Burning Man. he Pinhole Project exposes 30 x 40 inch sheets of light sensitive gelatin silver paper. We work with 12 pinhole cameras, created out of 50-gallon cardboard barrels. This size is uniquely suited for capturing the incredible scale and immense diversity of art and culture at Black Rock City. Under the red safelights of the darkroom, photosensitive paper is inserted into the camera body. Exposures range from 40 to 300 seconds, where concentrated beams of sunlight are funnelled through the pinhole and into the camera, creating a negative image of the recorded subject. We maintain a desert darkroom in a shipping container, where we gather to processes, develop and fix about one hundred photographs each Burning Man. These unique images are then exhibited in Illumination Village, Center Camp Cafe, and off-playa. The pinhole camp has been creating large-scale portraits with festival participants since 1999.

Play in the Desert Darkroom with Pinhole Project

18688

Illumination Village

Come develop photographs and play with us, we do pinhole photography! Pinhole Project invites you to help us in the Desert Darkroom! We maintain a full wet black and white photographic darkroom in a shipping container, where we gather to processes, develop and fix about one hundred photographs. Photographs made of paper with traditional chemicals and no digital input. The Pinhole Project exposes 30 x 40 inch sheets of light sensitive gelatin silver paper. We work with 12 pinhole cameras, created out of 50-gallon cardboard barrels. This size is uniquely suited for capturing the incredible scale and immense diversity of art and culture at Black Rock City. Under the red safelights of the darkroom, photosensitive paper is inserted into the camera body. Exposures range from 40 to 300 seconds, where concentrated beams of sunlight are funnelled through the pinhole and into the camera, creating a negative image of the recorded subject. We maintain a desert darkroom in a shipping container, where we gather to processes, develop and fix about one hundred photographs each Burning Man. These unique images are then exhibited in Illumination Village, Center Camp Cafe, and off-playa. The pinhole camp has been creating large-scale portraits with festival participants since 1999.

We are Story Telling Animals Seminar / Discussion

18748

Silicon Village

Stories: That’s how we have communicated, well I guess as long as we have been able to communicate. We used stories to pass on information, persuade, and entertain. Stories told by others give us insight into how they think and feel. When we hear something in a story that we connect with we don’t feel so alone in our own thoughts. Truth is, we are much more likely to remember something if we hear it in a story then just the facts. Humans are social beings and enjoy others for the most part and listing to stories gives us that connection. But what actually makes up a story? And better yet what makes up a compelling story that engages your audience? The Arts of Buon Fresco Revealed

18815

Guild Workshops -- At t...

Hi everyone, come and get PLASTERED! ;o) We humbly invite you all to “Becoming the Master/Mistress of Stones: The Arts of Buon Fresco!” Welcome to the Burning Man Guild Workshops! For the first time ever, Burning Man is hosting a series of workshops in a Florentine piazza-style format to have Masters of various craftsmanship skills teach our students the arts of the Renaissance. We, The Three Faced (Stone) Wench Workshop/Guild, are offering a series of classes you would love to attend! Here’s the scoop: Apprentices will learn the various actual old time techniques over several days to create a fresco (block) from scratch to take home. As part of our commitment to up-cycle, we will utilize and recycle actual (old foam insulation) building materials. Participants will learn to recreate various historical stone mixtures that compromise the the surfaces of the block, complete with plastering, cartooning, and finally the stages of painting the actual fresco with pigments. This artifact creation will be followed by (and applied) techniques to 'age' their artwork with the patina and craquelure of passing time. The result? A beautiful, yet portable and tangible, aged piece of buon fresco that becomes their momento of inspired learning at Burning Man. ;) Upon completing your fresco block, you will receive a Playa Plastered Master of Arts certificate, authorizing you to be plastered anywhere on the playa! That’s not all! We are offering a unique community project/event, and we invite everyone to participate with your hearts (and energy): We are accomplishing a recreation of Gustav Klimt’s Beethoven Frieze (Ode To Joy), with a slight twist on the theme: “All You Need Is Love.” The secco fresco artwork will stretch across several large panels, a moving tribute of the people lost at Orlando, Florida, and of our experiences at Burning Man. Please join us! ;o) Youth ages 12 and up welcome.

The Temple — Convertere [clothing optional]

18830

Naked Heart

<< The Temple >> We are each a temple [literally "place cut off," from stem of “tem” — to cut]. Inside each temple are housed experiences that are the basis of how we comprehend ourselves. The temple that we are is an adventure. In that adventure we are swimming through contradictions, polarity, wonder, desires, embarrassments; our emotions, feelings, curiosities, wounds, traumas. In the temple, what develops is the movement of the psyche. Maibel and Anthony serve as psychopomp guides through the temple with different exercises, taking participants on a trip that expands comprehension of their human complexity, our connection to each other, the need to explore the conversations that we never had. 　 　 << The Temple — Convertere >> You’ll engage in play that explores the unsaid. Go to where you can’t go alone. Reveal. Listen. Question. Vent. Return to yourself through each other. Convertere means converter, deriving from “turn around, transform, come-together, to turn, to return.” C/O* 　 　 << Your psychopomps >> Maibel was born in Caracas, Venezuela, and while residing in Buenos Aires, Argentina, she developed an acting process through the use of group research and play creation experience. She’s a permanent member of the Unknown Theater Group in Buenos Aires, which for 40 years has been a proponent of the Unknown Experience art form. Anthony organizes naturist and intimacy-building events in NYC and South Florida. His mentors include Christina Berkley, Guy Sengstock, John Thompson, Sean Wilkinson, Sara Ness, Amy Silverman, Jordan Myska Allen, Gina Brezini, and Nicole Daedone. We moderate a Facebook group called The Temple exploring the unknown, the unheard, the unsaid — and union. And another called Colony where we encourage conscious, smart, and progressive social nudism and sexuality. 　 *Clothing optional. Nudity is not a requirement.

Samasati Meditation

18836

Camp Contact

Samasati means awareness or consciousness. The purpose of this meditation is to bring awareness to the denial and fear people have regarding death. The goal of this meditation is to practice the art of witnessing rather than reaching to situations and circumstances. Be aware and remember that since you are alive, you must not take your life for granted. Choose the position: 'I will always value my life.' Appreciating my life means waking up every morning and looking into the mirror, and saying to myself, 'I am so happy to be alive!' Thank you Osho, for helping me to create this meditation." I designed this meditation so that it can be done in a group or by yourself. The first six stages are an oppertunity to practice dying consciously, a rehearsal for the end of your life. The remaining four stages are a reminder to live totally and cherish each moment.

The Zendo Project Workshop

18869

ReFOAMation

The Zendo Project provides a supportive environment and specialized care designed to transform difficult psychedelic experiences into valuable learning opportunities, and even potentially offer healing and growth. In turn, our work reduces the number of drug-related hospitalizations and arrests. This year, millions of people will use psychedelics outside of supervised medical contexts, many of them for the first time. Difficult psychedelic experiences can be frightening, but also potentially among the most valuable experiences someone can have. What can you do to help someone having a difficult psychedelic experience? What techniques are available for helping transform a potentially traumatic situation into a positive or even therapeutic one? What role has the Zendo Project played at festivals, and what take-home messages are available for others interested in psychedelic harm reduction?

The Temple — Nuptias [clothing optional]

18884

Naked Heart

<< The Temple >> We are each a temple [literally "place cut off," from stem of “tem” — to cut]. Inside each temple are housed experiences that are the basis of how we comprehend ourselves. The temple that we are is an adventure. In that adventure we are swimming through contradictions, polarity, wonder, desires, embarrassments; our emotions, feelings, curiosities, wounds, traumas. In the temple, what develops is the movement of the psyche. Maibel and Anthony serve as psychopomp guides through the temple with different exercises, taking participants on a trip that expands comprehension of their human complexity, our connection to each other, the need to explore the conversations that we never had. 　 　 << The Temple — Nuptias >> Can partners be more free together than apart? A new comprehension of polyamory and exclusivity: the Hermetic Relationship. C/O* 　 　 << Your psychopomps >> We—Anthony and Maibel—live the experience of returning to themselves through each other. We enjoy practices that stimulate these experiences that make us more vulnerable, more naked, more pure, more devoted. We moderate a Facebook group called The Temple exploring the unknown, the unheard, the unsaid — and union. And another called Colony where we encourage conscious, smart, and progressive social nudism and sexuality.

Exploring Conscious Touch

18958

Naked Heart

"We are all yearning for greater connection, yet often find ourselves lacking a place where we may explore while having our boundaries honored in each moment. Come co-create this special evening where we will be invited to find our ease in connection. Touch is a place where we as humans are often feeling a lack, but have an edge around asking for what we may desire or need. Let us create a container where all may be witnessed in their desire. A container where guilt, shame and fear around giving and receiving touch may be stripped away. Where we simply interact with consciousness and choice and that each honoring of another further honors ourselves. We will begin with a simple ceremony of seeing and being seen, so that we may drop into presence with one another. From there we will co-create our agreements and boundaries for the evening. Then we will engage in some guided massage, so that no one needs worry about skill or technique. We can all learn and explore together. Elemental massage is a beautiful way to welcome our bodies and explore differing kinds of activating and sensation touch. Know that you may choose to participate with a particular partner. All boundaries around partnership, touch and clothing will be honored. This is an evening of self-exploration, opening to our natural touch-positive nature in a way which is intended to open more pathways to self-love."

Morphic Field Movement

18965

Naked Heart

Movement precedes us, we don’t create movement. This practice is not dance, body expression, theater, nor performance — it is a composition of these, and more. We will use the intelligence of the movement to communicate. You can move being encouraged and guided by the intelligence of morphic fields (Rupert Sheldrake has published credible research about this). A morphic field is a field of energy that stores information; in the field exist dynamics, settings, games, processes; it is a memory field, it is an intelligent field. A morphic field is created when any of us introduces an intention and an action in space and time, which after being performed several times becomes a specific intelligence, then that intelligence influences the actions of a whole group and creates a memory of a way of doing things. We can create morphic fields at will, because our intelligence is able to. In a morphic field the communication is easy and instantaneous. What this workshop proposes is the creation of fields of intelligence through movement, because I believe that as human beings we are prepared to communicate with new languages. Art informs certain languages ​​that are developed over time, and perhaps now it's time to take those languages ​​as structures that allow us a different way to function in life. Morphic Field Movement becomes physical expression, borne from body languages, from the poetry of the body, from the clear expression of the bodies...

Contraexpression

18999

Naked Heart

Do you want to experience poetry of the body while hardly moving at all? Contraexpression is not passivity or the anti-expression; it’s 'contrary-expression' of any expressive stimulus, and it’s irresistible. There is no wrong way to do this. Open the door to your body to express the unimaginable. In the experience, you will be guided through a passage in which you find your own way of moving the body. I don’t ask anyone to move their body in a rhythm, nor engage bodies, nor expect that all the people do the same action. People don’t need to follow a pattern or imitate; it’s experiential, there is no wrong way to do this. I give directions based on trust in the body, and what it can manifest. The person will discover how to adapt these directions to their understanding and needs. Maybe someone can move rapidly, maybe another can move slowly, or hardly at all — each one with their own development and course of action. This workshop focuses on the method of “The Unknown Theater” (El Teatro Desconocido) directed by Juan Carlos De Petre and developed over forty years by a group of people concentrated on exploration of subtle expression. The practice reveals knowledge; we start from the consciousness of not-knowing — ignorance is the beginning. This knowledge is experimental and creative; not intellectual, preconceived, acquired through repetition, or memory. Participants will work as a unique being, independent, and according to their own development. You can overcome intimidation and shame; discover empowerment, physical malleability, and grace.

Merkaba: Tasting The Infinite Through Breath

19154

Camp Mystic

In this dynamic presentation & event participants will literally learn and practice how to 'plug themselves into the Infinite.' The intensity of the technique depends on the person, ranging from an incredible feeling of ecstasy, until space and time journeys. Being a technique that connects with the inner and higher self, it will also allows to experience breakthroughs, get answers about our lives, solve problems that we didn't even know to have. The more open to receive love and the more open minded we will be, the more we will get from this practice. The technique is as powerful as magical. Almost everybody that have experienced it, described it as mind blowing, many as life changing, some others as the most powerful moment of their life. Prepare to experience yourself in Totality!

Realtime authentic relating games

19167

Naked Heart

In this workshop we are going to play a few authentic relating games that center on connection. We stay in the present moment, report on our current experiences, and do our best to stay objective about the observations we make. For instance, if we want to only say things that are so objective that a camera could pick up on them, we might say "I notice your eyes are squinting and I see you are smiling" instead of "I see that you are happy". Because we don't know if that person is happy for sure, they could be putting on a face because they are nervous and afraid!

The Evolutionary Psychology of Polyamory

19314

Camp Mystic

Are human naturally monogamous or promiscuous? Neither view makes sense given what we've learned about human sexual psychology in the last couple of decades. Most of us seem to have evolved over the last million years to be polyamorous by nature. But we are socialized into monogamist mating norms that amplify sexual jealousy, reduce compersion, stifle our sexual sovereignty, and limit the social networks that we instinctively try to build through lovers and metamours. In this talk, a leading evolutionary psychology professor (author of 'The Mating Mind', 'Spent', and 'Mate') will give a quick, fun overview of the new science behind poly. Then we'll have a Q&A.

Trans 101 thru 401 with Dominique

19501

F & 7:45 - Camp Beavert...

The trans phenomenon. What do you know? What do you wish you knew? What would you like to know, but were afraid to ask. This purpose of this workshop is to educate and enlighten those interested in knowing more about this 3% of the public that few understand. This workshop seeks to help transphobic people... Not in a judgmental way... This is meant in a good way. The very basic definition transphobia, is simply being frightened of trans-folks because of misunderstandings or lack of education on all things trans. This is often because the questions you’ve always wanted to ask, are taboo; making it difficult to learn, understand, and honor the transgender path. Trans 101: The Nuts and Bolts. A brief PowerPoint discussion of definitions and the basics of gender, gender identity, gender expression, and sexual orientation. How are transgender and cisgender people alike? How are they different? Trans 201: A Peak Through the Veil. After learning the basics, we’ll have a Q&A session where any and all questions will be fielded. We all know that there are questions that are deemed inappropriate to ask a transperson. For this brief moment in time, there are no taboos. We will do our best to answer your questions with honesty, transparency, and sincerity. Trans 301: Dropping the Veil. We will bare our souls and our bodies for visual inspection and further Q&A. Trans 401: Shredding the Veil. For those brave audience members, we will open ourselves to not only visual review, but hands on, or hands in, examination.

Harvesting carbon and storing it in hemp buildings

19551

PlayaSkool

Leonardo knew about many of the uses of hemp ... It's a soil remediator and one of the fastest growing, most useful biomass crops for manufacturing that you can farm. Industrial hemp fibre crops harvest high volumes of carbon very quickly, so farming and building hemp housing is a very effective way to store carbon - each build locks up tonnes of it. The buildings are also thermally effective so you have reduced operational energy costs. The broad opportunities for value adding to fibre crops mean that wherever communities work together with farmers, they can potentially create major positive change.

Rule trading, making and printing

19703

Grand Elaborated Rule M...

Medieval Germany is known for the stories collected by Brothers Grimm, the Hanse trading company, people obeying to the rules of their kings, and Gutenbergs art of printing. All of these attributes are reflected in the G.E.R.M.A.N. guild workshop. This workshop is about rule making and printing. Following a playful structure, a personal rule of life and/or behavior is told and traded for a new rule, which is chosen or created by chance. To make this new rule a temporary or permanent part of the participants life, he or she can print this rule on pieces of old German files, badges, wristbands or even body parts.

Shamandome Camp

A deep dive into death, suffering and challenging fate through simple physical practices - opening the heart and accepting what life has to give. In many cultures death is seen as the unknown, the point at which it is difficult to determine what happens next. Will death be the end of life? The pain experienced in the lead-up to death or the manner death is portrayed may have lasting impressions on how we determine our own death. This workshop is about giving yourself a chance to look deeper into death with a clean slate. Determine your own method to prepare for death and live life with an openness to dying. Life Coaching Workshop

20060

IMAGINEnation

Did you ever notice that you and Al Roker (the weatherman) sound a lot alike? For example, he says, “tomorrow it’s going to rain; for the next five days it’ll be hot & muggy”. And, you say things like, “today sucked and I’m a procrastinator”, or “I’m not a morning person”, you know, “I’m cloudy with a chance of a storm”…as if you have nothing to do with it, it’s just how you and it is… But doesn’t weather reporting yourself into “not a morning person,” just gives you a doctor’s note from being nice until noon? We are all sneakily weather reporters in our lives, pretending we have no say over how we are going to be or how things are going to go. But what if it’s not so? Uh oh is right. What if you are actually the author of your life? I mean, who else is? In this workshop, you’ll begin to redefine a new and powerful context from which to run your personal and professional life, where you have a say over the weather.

Transcending Fear Workshop

20062

Trifucta

An existential exploration of Fear and EGO. Come learn how fear and our essential state of being work in a dynamic relationship to create our EGO (impulsive actions, and self-defeating beliefs and habits). In this workshop, we will touch on the basic understanding of fear and it's differentiation from Worry, Anxiety, and False Fear. Then dive deep into existentialism explaining why fear has such a programmable hold on our free will, and biology, causing our impulsive actions and thoughts. Then we will explore techniques I've used to transcend my own fears, self-defeating beliefs and habits, freeing myself from years of insecurity, blame, resentment, childhood abuse, guilt from molestation, and general self-hate. I will share every method that has worked for me, and then afterword we will have a Q&A, and have a fun conversation and share our experiences. About Me: Hello my name is Nine Johnson, I'm a Performance Anxiety coach in Los Angeles California. I usually work with Actors, Singers, Athletes, Directors and businesses people from all industries to identify and overcome their performance anxieties, insuring confidence and peak performance. I come from a spiritual and self development background with over 15 years experience, in counseling, and life coaching.

Geometrical Constructions

20157

Guild Workshops at the ...

The Rhombohedron Society is about exploring the world of cubic symmetry. The lesson being taught by the Society is about the unifying properties of the rhombic dodecahedrton. This includes finding and learning about the how the lost triangle of Pythagoras defines the slopes of the faces of cubic polyhedra. Within the space are four areas. The primary workshop/classroom includes seating and work tables where visitors will learn about the Lost Triangle and make a Lost Triangle template to take with them. Visitors also will have the opportunity to learn more about geometry by assembling small scale models. There will be a dome with built in seats and a transparent skin being used for 24/7 multi-media presentations, and the Gypsy Wagon and car “SV 3 Rose” all made in plywood with integral slotted and notched connections, more whimsical creations as if from the mind of Leonardo.

Soul Story Circle: Claiming Your Personal Myth

20282

What to expect from A Soul Story Circle: When we gather in a circle, one person is chosen to receive a story that will serve all. Latin Party

Our two “Maestros” will teach essential dance moves for each style… while enforcing the Latin proverb: Nobody cares how you dance, just do it with passion! This event will bring to life the deep connection that defines the Latin culture.

Shamata and Walking Meditation

20358

Naked Heart

Bring your neurotic mind, tame it, and go enjoy your burn having a sense of who the fuck you really are. Connect with your true grounded self. I have practiced this meditation by myself for about 2 years. I am curious to see how this will work in a group setting as this would be a new experience for me. It is an open-eye meditation technique that focuses on the breath while also taking in your surroundings. The walking meditation focuses on the sensation your feet feel while walking at a slow place in a small circle. This practice helps form a connection with the earth as a sense of grounding. With practice, this technique helps one discover who they really are, not who they feel they are supposed to be. It has done wonders for me and truly changed my life. The instructions are very brief and basic and each person's experience is unique.

Contact Improv : A Meditative Dance Technique

20587

Hello, We Love you!

Contact Improvisation is a meditative dance technique in which participants use points of physical contact to provide the starting point for exploration through movement. This contact can actually induce the production of a pair bonding hormone, called oxytocin, in the human brain, similar to how you feel when you hug or kiss a loved one. Through the sensation of touch and dance, you can explore organic movement generated through and with, one-another, forming new bonds and strengthening old ones. Accompanied by a variety of musicians, this session will begin with some simple guiding prompts to help individuals become familiar with touching as well as giving/receiving weight. As the jam progresses individuals get to explore movement by listening and responding to their partner/partners through touch. There are no right or wrong answers and you do not need prior dance training to participate. The central characteristic of Contact Improvisation is a focus on bodily awareness and physical reflexes rather than consciously controlled movements. Much like meditation, Contact Improvisational Dance seeks to honor the present moment by guiding the dancers to surrender what is happening now. “One learns to recognize and differentiate subtle impulses in our movement choices and our partner's choices. We begin to decipher the cues that we give and receive which tell us when to lead or follow, when to go up, when to go down, where to touch, how to lift, when to slow down, and when to be still. In this form one learns to stay in integrity with each choice, never forcing, never rushing. When Body, Mind, and Spirit are united in their instinctive wisdom one finds ones-self at home in every moment expressing ones true nature.” - Moti Zemelman

Mindfulness/Loving-Kindness Meditation

20615

Disco Chateau

Mindfulness and Loving-Kindness Meditation: Connecting to the Present Moment and Those Around Us. Mindfulness is paying attention in a particular way on purpose in the present moment, non-judgmentally. This first part of this experience will focus on practicing mindfulness and bringing a sense of inner calm and peace to participants. The 2nd part of this experience will focus on loving-kindness meditation, a form of meditation that is focused on building a habit of selfless or altruistic love. With compassion-focused meditation, participants will practice loving-kindness towards themselves and friends, family, and acquaintances, even total strangers.

Diversity at Burning Man

20623

Disco Chateau

Diversity at Burning Man: Connecting to the Larger Global Community. Recently, Burning Man has been criticized for its homogeneous population and its increasing income disparity issue. Despite being widely recognized around the world by different ethnic groups, faiths, and sexualities, Burning Man struggles to achieve representative diversity. Disco Chateau celebrates diversity and would like to share inclusion practices that have worked for us, as well as welcome others from different camps to discuss what has worked for them. This talk will invite community leaders to discuss Default World and On Playa empowerment, for a more diverse, inclusive and representative tomorrow.

Playa Glass

The Singer's Secret Weapon: THE KRACKLE

20695

Incandescence

Singers! If you want to build your voice to something magnificent, then you will need the krackle exercise! 'Tis the blood of a strong voice. It is not always the most appealing sound, especially for beginners, but sometimes you need to sound ugly before sounding awesome! The krackle is the rubbing together of the vocal chords, which gives you immense breath control, builds range, and give the sound extra resonance and brilliance. The krackle will get your voice anywhere you want it to take you. Once your voice has worked through the krackle, then it is ready to be garnished with other beauties, like breathy and flowy goodness. But for now were krackling it up!

What are those 5Rhythms anyway? w/Aaron Lifshin

20723

RhythmWave

Just like light, sound, or ocean waves, a dancing body moving freely passes through five distinct rhythmic patterns. These patterns continuously repeat themselves in a wave of motion. Gabrielle Roth's 5Rhythms® are: FLOWING – the fluid, continuous, grounded glide of our own movements; STACCATO – the percussive, pulsing beat that shapes us a thousand different ways; CHAOS – the rhythm of letting go, releasing into the catalytic wildness of our dance that can never be planned or repeated; LYRICAL – the rhythm of trance, where the weight of self-consciousness dissolves, where we lighten up and disappear into our own uniqueness; and STILLNESS – the quiet emptiness, where gentle movements rise and fall, start and end, in a field of silence. Please join Aaron Lifshin for an introduction to the 5Rhythms movement practice, at RhythmWave.

FOMO: Impacting decision making for centuries.

20837

Center Camp Cafe

"The fear of missing out (FOMO) is a new name for a concept deeply embedded in human nature: that by choosing to do something we're going to miss out on something else that is even better. In cognitive psychology FOMO is known as loss aversion. Loss aversion refers to people's tendency to strongly prefer avoiding losses to acquiring gains. Most studies suggest that losses are twice as powerful, psychologically, as gains. Basically FOMO is the losing out on what others are currently experiencing and valuing it higher than the gain of your current experience. An early example of FOMO comes from Tulipmania in Holland in the 1590s. Seeing and hearing others buy into the promises of tulip profitability encouraged others to do the same. Nobody wanted to be the one missing out. When you lose something it hurts and often to avoid this negative emotion strange behavior may occur. This talk will give insight into why FOMO occurs and illustrate that it happens not only to Millennials anxious about what experiences their peers are having, but also to those making business and investment decisions.

We’re creating a “digital world choir” out of human beings from across the planet, and from all walks of life, regardless of race, religion, nationality or social status. What does that mean exactly? Cultural Appropriation? Let's talk about it!

Golden Net, The

What can we do? • What does it mean to decolonize ourselves and why is it important to talk about it? • What hole are we seeking to fill? Contraexpression — Poetry of the Body

21059

Naked Heart

Do you want to experience poetry of the body while hardly moving at all? 　 　 Contraexpression is not anti-expression, passivity; it’s 'contrary-expression' of any expressive stimulus, and it’s irresistible. 　 　 There is no wrong way to do this. 　 　 In the experience, you will be guided through a passage in which you find your own way of moving the body. I don’t ask anyone to move their body in a rhythm, nor engage bodies, nor expect that all the people do the same action. People don’t need to follow a pattern or imitate; it’s experiential. 　 　 I give directions based on trust in the body, and what it can manifest. The person will discover how to adapt these directions to their understanding and needs. Maybe someone can move rapidly, maybe another can move slowly, or hardly at all — each one with their own development and course of action. 　 　 This workshop focuses on the method of “The Unknown Theater” (El Teatro Desconocido) directed by Juan Carlos De Petre and developed over forty years by a group of people concentrated on exploration of subtle expression. 　 　 The practice reveals knowledge; we start from the consciousness of not-knowing — ignorance is the beginning. 　 　 This knowledge is experimental and creative; not intellectual, preconceived, acquired through repetition, or memory. Participants will work as a unique being, independent, and according to their own development. You can overcome intimidation and shame; discover empowerment, physical malleability, and grace. 　 　 Open the door to your body to express the unimaginable. 　　 #clothing optional #nudist #naturist

Morphic Field Movement

21063

Naked Heart

This practice is not dance, body expression, theater, nor performance — it is a composition of these, and more. 　　 As human beings we are prepared to communicate with new languages. We will use the intelligence of the movement to communicate. You can move being encouraged and guided by the intelligence of morphic fields (Rupert Sheldrake has published credible research about this). 　　 A morphic field is a field of energy that stores information; in the field exist dynamics, settings, games, processes; it is a memory field, it is an intelligent field. A morphic field is created when any of us introduces an intention and an action in space and time, which after being performed several times becomes a specific intelligence, then that intelligence influences the actions of a whole group and creates a memory of a way of doing things. In a morphic field the communication is easy and instantaneous. 　　 Morphic Field Movement becomes physical expression, borne from body languages, from the poetry of the body, from the clear expression of the bodies. 　　 What I would like to explore is the possibility to express more subtle dimensions of communication, more rare to our usual life; communicating realities that words can not name and the body can reveal. Morphic Field Movement is a proposal to create another type of communication — alternative now, and I hope definitive and more popular in the future.　　 #clothing optional #nudist #naturist

Scale Mail Weaving

21197

Guild of Mile Higher Kn...

Ever wanted to learn the art of weaving scale mail into glorious, glimmering battle gear, costumes, jewelry, or other metal creations? If so, then this is the Renaissance workshop for you! Learn the basic weave for linking scales together, as well as a few advanced tips like creating a dart or a reinforced edge that you can apply to more complicated pieces. Weaving scale mail is a tedious process, so you won't be leaving with a new vest or shirt, but you should have a small piece (perhaps some earrings or a wrist cuff) that you made during the class that you can wear away to sparkle in the sun.

The box as art

21216

Cosmicopia & The Spoke ...

The box as art. Contemporary artists have used boxes in a variety of innovative ways. At face value, the box is a container: for shoes, clothes, a myriad of utilitarian purposes. In the hands of the artist, the box becomes a sculptural form. Inside and outside, the sculptural box is a container for place, memory, and emotion. This talk will provide a survey of how artists have successfully used boxes to create art and inspire attendees to create their own boxes fueled by their experiences in Black Rock City. Speaker: Shimmera. Shimmera (aka Cheryl Patrice Derricotte in the default world) is a visual artist and her primary medium is glass. This is her 3rd trip home to Black Rock City and she is the guest visual arts instructor for the three-credit California Institute of Integral Studies’ class “Art and Survival: Radical Creation at Burning Man.

Creative Visualization: Picture your future

21225

Dr Feelgood Advice Boot...

Join us for a guided creative visualization meditation. We will help you picture the perfect day 10 yrs in your future. The process works by subconsciously shifting your decision making over the next 10 years eventually making your vision a reality. You don't know what that day looks like? Don't worry, most people don't, but your subconscious already knows what is important to it. The more amazing and compelling the vision that you let emerge, the more you will be drawn to it. How? Most people make between 80 to 400 decisions a day. A rich, compelling visualization with a lot of sensory "hooks" can shift those decisions towards your perfect future because the right choices will feel "right". We will start with a mindfulness of breath meditation, a gratitude exercise and then wake up the morning of your perfect day and explore it through a guided process. After, we will ask a few of those interested to share their visualization with the group. We look forward to sharing your future day together. Dr.Feelgood
